title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Put in a casserole dish, 9 x 11-inch.
Mix soup with 1 can milk; put over beef.
Sprinkle cheese over top; then place Tater Tots on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and stir well until blended.
Divide mixture evenly.
Pour in two 9-inch buttered pie plates and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out center.
Whip with mixture with salt, pepper and margarine.
Add milk slowly until a little stiffer than mashed potatoes.
Fill shells.
Cover with grated cheese.
Do not overbake at serving time.
Sprinkle on top with paprika.
Bacon bits may be added if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
I use Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Great hot or cold.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture clings together.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Beat together eggs, granulated sugar and lemon juice.
Sift together the 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: sunshine rice salad
directions: Combine rice and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat to low.
Let steam 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: raisin ice water pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers as for bread and butter pickles.
Sprinkle salt over top.
Add ice cubes to cover.
Let stand 3 hours (add onion and red pepper, if desired).
Drain well.
Put raisins in enough water to barely cover.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and bring to a boil.
When green color goes, pack in jars and seal.
Be sure some raisins get in each jar.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Blend flour, salt, pepper and gradually add milk and cheese.
Stir over medium heat until smooth and slightly thickened.
Stir in sour cream and cooked noodles until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately or place in baking dish and broil until brown.
Serves four.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form small balls (1/2-inch). Place in shallow pan.

title: vegetable centerpiece
directions: You will also need one 18-inch foam cone.

title: holiday chocolate butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except flour and cocoa.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls as desired (1-inch balls, 2 to 3-inch logs, balls flattened, balls with indentations, etc.) or use cookie press.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheets. Bake for 7 to 9 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Decorate with melted chocolate chips, melted almond bars, nuts, colored sugars, candied fruit, candies, maraschino cherries, etc.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: creamy mocha fudge
directions: In heavy pan, over low heat, melt chips with all milk, coffee and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly into foil lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill for 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off foil.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli.
Drain and cut up large pieces. Combine corn, cheese and soup.
Fold in cooked vegetables and mushrooms.
Turn mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Toss bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on whole wheat toast or fill scooped out tomato.
You choose the condiments and enjoy.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop corn in oil and pour in large roasting pan.
Boil for 5 minutes oleo, brown sugar and add vanilla and soda.
Mix well. Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and stir every 15 minutes.
Store in tight container.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all the preceding ingredients together and form into a loaf.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Cream with mixer the margarine and sugar.
Add salt, vanilla and flour.
Fold in chocolate bits and chopped nuts.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Freeze on tray. Then store in plastic bags.

title: apricot soda
directions: Stir together the cocoa powder and apricot nectar or orange juice.
Divide mixture into 3 tall glasses.
To each glass add 1 or 2 scoops of ice cream or ice milk; stir gently.
Carefully pour about 1/2 cup carbonated beverage down the side of each glass. Serve immediately with straws.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Stir in cornmeal gradually and cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
To corn meal mixture, add butter, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Mix well.
Then, in large mixing bowl, add hot mixture slowly to beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly. Fold in egg white.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in hot, preheated 425° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve at once with butter.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coca-cola barbecue sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lift meat from marinade and place on foil in roasting pan (enough foil to cover and envelope wrap). Roast for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add applesauce and soda while apples are warm.
Beat in 1 egg at a time; add flour and spices, then add nuts and raisins dredged in 1/2 cup of the flour.
Bake 2 hours in moderate oven (about 315°).

title: crab dip in chafing dish
directions: Heat cream cheese on top of stove.
Add crab, lime juice and couple dashes of hot sauce and a teaspoon salt.
Stir while heating.
When heated well, stir in pecans.
Serve in chafing dish with crackers.

title: lentil-rice casserole
directions: Blend all together in a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 300 for 2-2-1/2 hours.
During the last 20 minutes, you may top with 1/2 c grated cheddar cheese if desired.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together and cream with margarine.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add milk, juice and rind.
Mix beaten egg whites into liquid and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until "set" as custard.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine.
Add hash browns, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Pour into large casserole.
Mix corn flakes and melted margarine together and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet until covered.
Bake until light brown and then cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together and spread on rolls.
Top with any of the other items listed (chopped in little pieces).
Top with cheese last and press down.
Refrigerate and then cut into bars.
Will make 1 large cookie sheet or 2 small sheets.

title: guatemalan black beans
directions: Mince the onion, garlic cloves (and pepper, if using). Add enough olive oil to barely cover the skillet. Saut the seasoning veggies until soft. Open, drain and wash the black beans. Add them to the skillet once onion, etc. is translucent and cook until almost dry. You can slightly mash the beans or even put them in the blender for a few seconds.

title: dorothy reed's germantown cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift in dry ingredients.
Add oats and coconut last.
Mix well.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Butter and lightly flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate fresh coconut in hand grater or food processor to make 3 cups.
Cream shortening and slowly add sugar.
Beat until light and smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Stir in almond extract.
Sift dry ingredients into separate bowl.
Add alternately in 3 parts with milk until well blended.
Stir in one cup coconut.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Stir one-third of egg whites into batter.
Gently fold in remainder.
Pour batter into cake pans. Bake 25 minutes.
Insert toothpick in center to make sure cake is done.
Let layers cool 10 minutes in pans, then remove to cake racks to finish cooling.
Frost with 7-Minute Frosting.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add green chiles, soups and sauce.
Stir until well mixed.

title: pineapple-chocolate fleck cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl. Stir in chocolate, nuts and raisins. Add slightly beaten eggs, melted butter and crushed pineapple.
Mix just to moisten flour.
Pour into a 9-inch tube pan which has been greased and then lined on the bottom with waxed paper. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 15 minutes, then remove from pan and finish cooling on rack. For easier slicing and mellowing of flavors, store cake overnight wrapped in wax paper, plastic wrap or aluminum foil.

title: dan patch pancakes
directions: Beat sour cream and cottage cheese together.
Add eggs, flour, sugar, salt and soda.
May be mixed in blender.
Cook as usual.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour sifted with cream of tartar and soda.
Add vanilla. Roll into balls.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until they turn a light tan.
You can frost for Christmas.

title: whole wheat bread(from the family of leah macleod)
directions: Beat 100 strokes with wooden spoon.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups more of whole wheat flour and 1 1/2 to 2 cups white flour.
Knead in flour for 15 to 20 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Punch down. Divide in 2.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheese 'n' turkey enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in dressing over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in turkey, 1/4 cup of the picante sauce, the cream cheese and the cumin.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Size of shrimp can be your preference.
Mix all ingredients. Place in covered container and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Can be kept for a week.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in pan.
Cover with ice.
Put salt on top of ice.
Let set for 3 hours.
Remove ice and rinse lightly.

title: alda's granola
directions: Mix oatmeal, coconut, dates, wheat germ and sliced almonds in large bowl.
Place salt, vanilla, oil, water and brown sugar in blender.
Blend together until well mixed, then mix everything together in the large bowl.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: aaron's fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add eggs and cook until done, but not dry.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons grease. Cook onion until tender. Stir in rice, soy sauce, eggs and bacon bits.
Keep warm.

title: crisp pickles
directions: Slice pickles, onions, peppers and garlic. Cover with ice cubes-drain. Combine other ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture. Heat just to a boil. Seal in hot jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Peel skin and put in mixing bowl. Mash with potato masher.
Combine potatoes with half and half and melted butter.
Mix until fluffy.

title: quick fudge
directions: Put in bowl and put in microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Take out, mix well and let set.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Place unpeeled potatoes in microwave-safe dish.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes, rotating dish once.

title: basic waffle recipe
directions: Heat waffle baker.
Sift together dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Combine egg yolks and milk; stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in cooking oil.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Carefully fold in egg whites, leaving a few little fluffs.
Do not overmix.
Bake in preheated waffle baker until golden brown.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar together.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and coffee and mix well.
Add the raisins and nuts. Pour into large cookie sheet (greased and floured) and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
When cool, frost with any favorite glaze or sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Melt butter.
Mix with other ingredients except egg whites.
Mix all ingredients together, then fold in egg whites.
Pour into souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water (until frothy, not stiff). Stir in pecans until well coated (add more pecans if needed to use up all the egg mix). Mix cinnamon, sugar and salt, and add to pecans. Stir until pecans are completely coated. Line a large cookie sheet with foil. Spread pecans in single layer. Bake at 225 degrees for 1 hour. Stir about every 15 minutes.

title: mabel's crock pickles
directions: Wash, drain and cover cucumbers with cold salt brine, strong enough to float an egg (use canning salt; 2 cups salt to 1 gallon water).
Weight down and let stand 3 weeks.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; cook until done.
Add any kind of vegetables you want.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Cook stew meat in water until tender.
Add the Veg-All and tomato soup; stir.
Simmer for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: very easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add the rest of the ingredients. Bring to a full boil, stirring frequently.
Done in 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Add next 2 ingredients. Line pan with tortillas. Top with hamburger mixture and cheese. Make 2 or 3 layers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add crushed pineapple, 1/2 cup of nuts, onion, seasoned salt and green pepper.
Form into a ball and add remaining nuts to outside.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Place chops and sauerkraut in large pan.
Add water.
Boil gently 40 minutes.
Combine Bisquick and milk.
Spoon dough in mounds on top of boiling sauerkraut.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: bobbie's vegetable casserole
directions: Put in stalk of celery and onion; cook together.
Cook vegetables until done.
Drain of liquid.
Put layer of vegetables, then half of cheese, then bread crumbs.
Pour half melted oleo and repeat with another layer, with crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overcook zucchini.
Strain to get rid of water.

title: cool-light dessert
directions: When mixing pudding, use only 1/2 of the milk called for. Layer ladyfingers on bottom of 13 x 13-inch pan then spread on pistachio pudding (make sure you only used 1/2 of the milk recommended) then another layer of ladyfingers then another layer of pistachio pudding then top it with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed Heath bar on top or crushed nuts.

title: czech kolackies
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk and sugar; let set for about 5 minutes. Add 5 cups of sifted flour.
Mix well.
Let set in a warm place for about 1/2 hour.
Add egg yolks, shortening, salt and rest of flour.
Mix and knead well (needs to be a soft dough).
Let set in a warm place for an hour, until doubled in bulk.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat together eggs, 1 cup softened margarine (not melted) and powdered sugar for 15 minutes - NO LESS.
Mix together graham crackers and melted margarine.
Spread out in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Pour egg mixture over crust and slice bananas (sprinkle with lemon juice to maintain color).
Put banana slices on top of egg mixture. Place drained pineapple pieces over bananas.
Cover with whipped topping and decorate with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter; add onion.
Saute 20 minutes.
Add paprika, pepper, bay leaves and flour.
Stir; mix well over low heat.
Add small amount of bouillon and cook for 5 minutes.
Gradually add rest of bouillon; simmer for 30 minutes or place all ingredients in crock-pot for several hours.
Place slice of French bread in bowl and shredded Provolone or Gruyere cheese.
Brown under broiler.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Thaw apple juice concentrate.
Combine (undiluted) with flour and cinnamon in container with tight lid.
Shake well.
Pour into saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens. Remove from heat.
Add peeled, sliced apples to hot mixture; stir to coat.
Spoon into pie shell.
Top with second crust.
Bake as usual for other apple pies.

title: never fail layer cake
directions: Stir flour, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour, one cup at a time, to mixture alternating with milk.
Beat batter until smooth and creamy. Add flavoring.
Bake in three 9-inch pans 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: millionaire dressing
directions: Mix, except oil.
Then slowly add the oil while beating.
Let salad dressing stand for 24 hours before serving.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Saute celery in a little butter to soften.
Mix everything together.
Add a little milk, if it seems stiff.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes, until brown.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix dough and roll to 1/2-inch or 3/4-inch thickness.
Place biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: 9 day cole slaw
directions: Pour 2 tablespoons sugar and celery seed over the vegetables. Heat remaining ingredients to boiling, let cool until still warm. Pour over vegetables and let cool.
Put into refrigerator.
Let set for at least 24 hours.
Gets better every day and will keep for 9 days.

title: pizza
directions: Grease pizza pan.
Roll out biscuits.
Place on pan like a crust.
Piece together.
Spread Pizza Quick over the biscuits. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over Pizza Quick.
Place toppings as you like them, then sprinkle on the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly and brown.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Cook onion in butter until transparent.
Add salt and paprika; add cut up chicken and mix to coat chicken.
Add water to cover chicken; boil until chicken is tender.
Skim fat, then thicken gravy with flour.
Add sour cream, making sure not to overboil; simmer until sour cream is well dissolved into the gravy.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread on bottom and sides of pan. Make crumb mixture from next 3 ingredients.
Layer apples and crumb mixture, making sure top layer is crumbs.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Place pan on cookie sheet or pizza pan (pie will bubble over).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook on medium heat, stirring all the time, until thick and clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla until soft mounds form.
Add sugar very gradually, beating well.
Add cooled cornstarch mixture, then beat until stiff.
Spread on lukewarm pie and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine and vinegar.
Let stand while beating eggs.
Add sugar and the vinegar and butter to the eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: seafood party squares
directions: Mix in order given.
Heat oven to 375°.
*Pour mixture in greased pan.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut in squares.

title: mustard-honey coated chicken
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in baking pan.
Place chicken in pan and cover with sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn and baste several times!

title: marinade for any cut of lamb(up to 5 pounds)
directions: Combine in a saucepan.
Bring all to a simmer and baste the lamb while cooking.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Mix and heat soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper until blended.
Layer carrots, bell pepper and onion.
Pour marinade over.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir occasionally.
(Keeps a week or so.)

title: okra pickle
directions: Pack
okra
in hot sterilized jars.
Put a garlic clove in each jar.
Heat water, vinegar, salt, dill seed and pepper to boiling
point.
Pour
boiling
brine
in
jars
and seal. Process in water bath at simmering, temperature about 180° to 200°
for 10	minutes.
Let
ripen
for
several weeks before opening. Makes about 4 pints.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Thoroughly wipe the mushrooms clean with a soft cloth. Place them in a saucepan; cover them with the
dressing and simmer over a medium-low burner for 15 minutes. Chill and drain the mushrooms, saving

the dressing to store any leftover mushrooms in. (You can even simmer another batch of mushrooms in it when the first batch is gone.) Arrange the mushrooms on lettuce with toothpicks for spearing. Yield: Depending on the size of your mushrooms, this will make about 12 to 15 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, melted margarine and peanut butter.
Roll into small balls and dip into melted chocolate chips and wax.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: eleanor's ice cream
directions: Combine
milk,	water, sugar and eggs in double boiler. Cool until
it
steams (do not boil!).
Add fruit or flavoring as desired.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Follow instructions on package of cake mix.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Boil exactly 1 minute.
Beat until creamy. Spread between layers and on top of the cake.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti, then pour the Italian dressing over the hot spaghetti and stir well.
Cool in the refrigerator.
When the spaghetti mix is cooled, add the dry dressing mix and veggies. Stir very well and let marinate several hours.
Make this in early a.m.

title: coconut icing
directions: Boil sugar and water until it thickens.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup into the egg whites, beating all the time.
Add vanilla, then coconut.
Mix in half coconut and sprinkle the other half on the cake.

title: tropical pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy. Add baking powder and beat some more. Add sugar; beat until stiff. Fold in crackers and pecans. Pour into buttered pie pan. Bake 25 minutes. Top with 1 package of Dream Whip mixed as directed. Let cool before eating.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper, then drain.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased sheet pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven and place small butter pats over entire top of cornbread.
Cover with foil and bake 15 additional minutes at same temperature.

title: wisconsin beer brats
directions: Put brats and 1/2 to 1 whole sliced onion in large kettle, cover with beer, 2 to 3 cans.
Boil 30 to 40 minutes until brats turn a sort of white.
Let sit in kettle for a minute or two.
Take kettle to hot charcoal grill and put brats on grill.
As they brown, take them off and put them back in the beer and onion sauce. Serve from kettle on hot dog buns with horseradish mustard and the works and the rest of the beer.
Great for summertime cookout.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into tart shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 tarts.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter gently for 2 minutes.
Dissolve beef cubes in hot water.
Melt butter and blend with flour in another pan. Add cream, salt, pepper, beef broth and mushrooms to butter and flour mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole. Top with cheese and crumbs mixed together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook beef slowly until gray.
Drain off fat.
Put in large soup pot.
Add tomatoes; if whole tomatoes, cut 4 or 5 times with scissors, while still in can.
Pour all vegetables and juice in soup pot.
Stir in beef stew seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil, then cut down and simmer about two (2) hours.
Put in container and freeze.
Makes about 5 quarts.
Do not add salt to this recipe. When serving, may add 1 large can V-8 juice to this recipe.
I sometimes add 2 to 4 tablespoons sugar.

title: chocolate chow mein "haystacks"(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole or large bowl, place chocolate pieces. Cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium or Low 4 to 5 1/2 minutes until melted.
Stir chocolate until smooth; add noodles and using 2 forks, toss to coat well.
On strips of foil or wax paper, form into 1 1/2-inch clusters.
Cool to set.
Can spray (butter) on dish.
Makes about 24 (1 1/2-inch) Haystacks.

title: caramel nut monkey bread
directions: Take the rolls from the freezer; put them in the refrigerator 12 hours ahead of time.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Saute the onion and parsley.
In a large bowl combine the beef, potatoes and milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a mixing bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg yolks until thick.
Blend the yolks into the beef mixture.
Fold in the egg whites.
Transfer the mixture to a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Empty pistachio pudding into salad container.
Add pineapple; stir until well mixed.
Add Cool Whip; stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Stir until well mixed.
Let stand in refrigerator one hour.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Place in freezer containers (quart and pint). To serve, thaw in refrigerator if possible. Store leftovers in glass jars with lid and refrigerate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together; add carrots.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked grits
directions: While grits are hot, melt butter and cheese in it.
Place eggs in measuring cup and add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add milk and eggs to grits mixture.
Pour into a casserole and bake in moderate oven for about 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and boil over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, chicken and soup together and put in a large baking pan.
Mix together the margarine, flour and milk and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: chicken salad on a croissant
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise on each side of a croissant.
Spread the chicken salad on the croissant.
Serve with fruit.

title: roasted red pepper dip
directions: In food processor or blender, mix all ingredients until smooth.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: acini salad(pasta salad)
directions: Cook acini according to package directions.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges, set aside in refrigerator to cool overnight. Save juice.
Cook until thick:
juice, sugar, flour, eggs (beaten) and salt.
Pour over acini while hot.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and put in greased loaf pan and bake in 300° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hershey's milk chocolate cake
directions: Combine chocolate bar, butter or margarine and boiling water in medium bowl.
Stir to melt chocolate.
Combine flour, brown sugar, soda and salt in a large bowl; gradually add chocolate mixture, beating until thoroughly blended.
Blend in eggs, sour cream and vanilla; beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely and frost as desired.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes (approximately 1/4 inch).
Salt and pepper lightly.
Sprinkle on flour.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove stems from mushrooms to make small crevice for stuffing.
Wash mushrooms and roll in butter.
Place upright in baking dish.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients, reserve 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese for topping.
Press mixture in crevice of mushrooms and top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until hot.
Can be made in advance and frozen.
Remaining mixture and mushroom stems are great in salad.

title: recipe for a happy church
directions: Take love and loyalty and mix thoroughly with faith.
Blend in tenderness, kindness and understanding.
Add friendship and hope; sprinkle abundantly with laughter.
Bake with sunshine and serve daily with generous helpings.
This will not only make a happy church, but it will also make a happy home.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Pour off some of the grease.
Add vinegar and sugar and stir.
Bring to boil.
Add 1 cup water with 3 tablespoons cornstarch (dissolved).
Stir until thick.
Pour over cooled, sliced potatoes.
Crumble bacon and onion on top and mix well, tossing gently.
Put in oven before serving.
Serve warm and enjoy.

title: italian sauce for lasagne
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery.
Add rest of the ingredients and simmer for about 3 hours.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Pat out and bake at 375° until brown, about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: debbie's banana pudding
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients until thick.
Blend Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip with pudding mixture.
Layer pudding mixture with bananas and vanilla wafers.
The best ever!!!

title: smothered rutabagas or turnips
directions: Saute ground pork or beef and pour off the fat.
Meanwhile, in a separate pan, saute onions in margarine, then add turnips or rutabagas.
Cook down (may need to add some water).
Fold in the cooked meat and season with salt, pepper and sugar.

title: coffee bars
directions: Combine raisins, coffee and cinnamon; let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to cake batter.
Last, add cinnamon and raisins.
Spread batter in jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Spread with glaze of confectioners sugar and coffee while still warm.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Chop fruit and nuts and combine.
Mix dry ingredients over fruit.
Cream the oleo and sugar until fluffy. Add egg and mix.
Slowly add flour/fruit mixture to blend. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Mix sliced peaches and 1/2 cup sugar to sweeten and set aside. Mix melted oleo, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, milk and baking powder together for a smooth cake like batter. Pour batter in a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour sweetened peaches over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.
Is delicious.

title: browned butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook butter over medium heat just until light brown; watch closely, butter burns easily.
Mix sugar, nuts and flour together.
Gently stir in egg whites, then hot butter. Generously butter petite heart pan.
Fill each pan halfway.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan. (Sides may need to be loosened with a spatula.)

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie roll and layer on pizza pan.
Bake and cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over the cooled crust. Layer with sliced fruit of your choice.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Put in a large bowl the shortening, sugar, egg and molasses. Beat on medium speed.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until blended. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Blend in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk and vinegar.
Stir in pecans, cherries and dates. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake at 400° on greased cookie sheet. Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful of dough 2-inches apart.
Top each with pecan half. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice according to directions.
In a large saucepan, melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Add mushrooms and saute 1 minute.
Add flour and stir.
Add chicken stock, lemon juice and wine. Stir slowly until mixture thickens. Add parsley, tarragon and cheese and stir.
Combine cooked rice, shrimp and sauce. Spoon into 2-quart casserole and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cover and cook 15 minutes more, if needed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix
all
ingredients in small casserole.
Sprinkle top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans and bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool and add confectioners sugar mixed with softened cream cheese. Spread this over crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Finish with Cool Whip.
Top with chopped nuts and cherries if you like.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: About 1 hour before serving, melt butter in a 425° oven in a pan large enough to lay pieces in a single layer.
Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper and coat chicken evenly.
Place skin-side down in melted butter.
Bake for 30 minutes, turn and bake 15 minutes longer or until chicken is done.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix water and coffee. Add boiling water and combine thoroughly. Let cool completely. Add vodka and pour into a 1/2-gallon jar. Drop in vanilla bean. Cover and let stand for 30 days (under the sink). Strain and use.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers and onions together; pour boiling water over all.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Drain in colander.
Place in pot and add sugar, flour, vinegar, prepared mustard and margarine or butter. Cook for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Chill ingredients in refrigerator the day before opening. Mold ice ring with slices of lemon, lime and mint.
Combine ginger ale and apple juice and pour in punch bowl.
Center ice ring in the center.

title: gladys' original corny casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Put in casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover top with mild, grated cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Saute onion in melted oleo.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until well blended.
Add rice and broccoli. Mix.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumb topping. Bake at 375° approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over Jello.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and 1/2 cup juice from strawberries.
Mix and let gel set till soft.
After set, beat with electric mixer till very fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Add strawberries and beat some more.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Using a loaf pan, layer, starting with Jello mix, then cake, and repeat ending up with Jello mix.
Chill overnight or 24 hours.
Enough Jello may be put in bottom of pan chilled stiffly for a nicer look when serving (about 3/4 c.).
You may add 1/2 c. chopped maraschino cherries on top.

title: granny sims white fruit cake
directions: Cut fruits and nuts coarsely and flour with 1 cup of flour (reserve some fruits and nuts whole for decorating).
Cream sugar and butter in mixer; add eggs 1 at a time.
Add flour, spices and wine, alternating.
Add jam and stir.
Add fruits and nuts; stir. Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease 2 tube pans and line with brown paper bag.
Bake 3 hours.
Decorate 1 hour before done.
Let stand in pans overnight.

title: granny's spaghetti sauce
directions: Dice onion; brown in a heavy skillet, using lard or oil.
When onion is almost brown, add sugar and salt.
Finish browning.
Add tomatoes; cook to a thick sauce.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix in margarine (melted).
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: indigestion
directions: Chop ingredients, add to Ro-Tel.
Makes a great appetizer for Mexican dishes.
Serve with chips.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Cook potatoes with skins.
Next day, mash well with salt, eggs and flour.
Mix all together.
Brown bread crumbs with a little margarine in frying pan.
Put some in middle of potato dumplings, roll in flour and press together.
Good to form dumplings.
Bring some water to a boil with a little salt.
Put wire basket in pan. Drop dumplings in hot water.
When they rise to top, let them boil 3 minutes.
Remove.
Next day, cut dumplings in half and brown in frypan.
Pour gravy and meat over them.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze thawed spinach thoroughly, until dry.
Combine dry soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise, blending all ingredients well.
Add coarsely chopped water chestnuts and scallions to mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Makes 4 cups.

title: spaghetti mosca
directions: Combine onion, basil and parsley and saute in oleo and olive oil.
Add cooked spaghetti and stir until well coated.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sliced zucchini pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil; pour over zucchini and onion and let stand 1 hour.
Bring to a boil; cook for 3 minutes (do not overcook).
Pack in hot, sterilized jars. Process at 212° for 5 minutes.

title: cherry delite
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese; mix until lumps are almost gone.
In a long casserole dish, put a layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding mix, then a layer of cherries.
Repeat until all is gone. Take a few graham crackers and crush up fine; sprinkle over top.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix all together except cheese.
When you serve, sprinkle some cheese on top of each serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast sandwich
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bread.
Spread mixture evenly between 8 slices of bread, forming 4 sandwiches.
Spread melted butter on outside surface of sandwiches.
Brown both sides in a skillet and serve.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: I use a large, black iron frypan for this recipe.

title: veal sandwich spread(kalve-sus)
directions: Boil meat in salted water until done.
Grind meat and put it back in broth; let it come to a boil.
Add gelatin.
Season to taste.
When cold, slice and serve.
Tastes good with lefse or flatbread.

title: zucchini with tomatoes
directions: *Can use 2 cups fresh peeled tomatoes plus 3/4 cup water instead of the canned tomatoes.
tags: Recipe Secrets golden onion soup mix

title: peanut brittle
directions: Add sugar, Karo syrup and cold water.
Cook until temperature reaches 236° on candy thermometer.
Then add raw peanuts and cook until peanuts pop and turn somewhat yellow around 300°.
Stir in baking soda and quickly stir well, then pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Break up pieces when cool.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and pineapple; bring to a boil, then add cream cheese and water.
Jell slightly.
Add Cool Whip and put back in refrigerator to jell hard.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix well with a fork, then knead on floured table top for ten minutes.
Kneading is important.
Roll out thin on floured board and cut into strips, using just enough flour to keep dough from sticking.
Cook in boiling chicken broth or beef broth.

title: balsamic salad dressing
directions: In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine all ingredients; shake well.
Store in the refrigerator, shake before each use.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat chicken broth and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix oleo, flour and buttermilk; pour over chicken.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°, then 10 minutes at 400° to brown.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut up onion, carrots and potatoes into bite-size pieces. Place meat into casserole; put vegetables on top of meat.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Combine soup and wine; pour over top.
Cover with foil and casserole lid.
Put in 250° oven for 5 hours.
This can also be made in a crock-pot.

title: fish fillets on spinach
directions: Wash fish; pat dry.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and let stand for 10 minutes.
Wash spinach well.
Chop coarsely.
Heat oil in frypan.
Add onion; saute until soft.
Fry fish in pan with onions a few minutes on each side until golden brown.
Remove fish and onions; reserve.
Add spinach to frypan and stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes.
Grease casserole dish with butter; add spinach.
Arrange fish on spinach; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place tomatoes on fish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Great!

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed (omit butter).
Brown sausage and drain. Mix rice and sausage.
Add mushrooms and saute.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vegetable oil. Add flour, baking powder and orange juice. Have apples peeled and sliced. Sprinkle them with 2 teaspoons of cinnamon that has been mixed with 5 tablespoons sugar. Put half the cake mixture into a greased and floured tube pan. Cover with half of the apple mixture. Add the rest of the batter and top with remaining apple slices. Chopped walnuts may be sprinkled on top, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until done.

title: soda fountain punch
directions: Combine coffee and sugar in large bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in soda and ice cream.
Makes 14 servings in punch glasses or 6 to 8 servings in tall glasses.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast into water; let stand a few minutes.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour hot milk over one cup of butter, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, eggs and half of the flour.
Beat well.
Add enough flour to make dough that will not stick to the bowl.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 40 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and beat together well.
Pour into unbaked pie-crust-lined pan.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from edge comes out clean.

title: *custard baked in phyllo dough
directions: Combine sugar, farina and eggs.
Heat milk (use your microwave) and slowly add it to the egg mixture, stirring continuously, until mixture thickens (use low heat).
Add butter and vanilla.
Allow to cool.
Cut your filo into quarters.
Butter, fold and butter. Place about 1 teaspoonful of the farina mixture at one end.
Fold in sides and roll up.
Butter end and seal.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes until crisp and lightly browned. Pour a little cool syrup over the warm pastry.
Yields approximately 48.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add 7-Up.
Add rest of ingredients and let set, then cover with following topping.

title: rachel's hot chicken salad
directions: Put rice, celery and onions in casserole for 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Combine rice, chicken, peas, celery, green peppers and onion. Combine remaining ingredients and toss with chicken mixture. Chill before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into ice cream freezer. Add enough milk to finish filling freezer. This can also be used to make pineapple and peach. Just use the peach or pineapple jello and fruit.

title: coconut crackers
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll out thin on cookie sheet.
Prick with fork.
Cut dough into desired size before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done. Serve with apricot jam made by chopping dry apricots (unsweetened) into boiling water and cooking until desired texture.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil carrots 10 minutes.
Drain and put in baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Melt cheese and margarine together and pour over carrots.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Place potatoes into heavy saucepan with water and salt.
Cover tightly and bring to a boil.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, salt and garlic. Fold sauce into potatoes.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and top is slightly brown.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk; stir well.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla and melted oleo.
Add dates and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Center should be firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: green bean lyonnaise
directions: Trim the beans.
Blanch the beans for 6 minutes in boiling water.
Fry the bacon in a large skillet.
Drain the grease.
Add the butter, onion and pimento.
Saute until tender.
Add the beans.
Fast fry for 3 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add strawberries.
Stir and chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour half into a 9-inch square dish.
Chill until almost firm.
Stir sour cream into the remaining jello and pour over other jello in dish. Chill until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Put soda in sour cream.
Mix salt and flour.
Alternate flour and sour cream.
Add flavorings last.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Leave in pan to cool for 1 hour.

title: corn bread loaf
directions: In skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Stir in onions and celery.
Saute for 8 minutes, or until soft.
In large bowl, combine corn bread crumbs and bread crumbs.
Stir in onion mixture and the next 4 ingredients.
Stir in eggs and chicken broth. Spoon evenly into greased and floured 4 x 12-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until top is brown.
Unmold onto serving plate
and slice.
Serve immediately.
Serves 10.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff. Stir in chips and vanilla.
Mix well to coat.
Drop on ungreased, foil lined pan.
Place in oven and turn off at once.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Put in pan. Combine brown sugar, oatmeal and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Cut in butter and Crisco.
Cover rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: brandied fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in with butter, egg and sugar mixture. Fold in 1 cup chopped nuts and 2 cups brandied fruit.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour.

title: connie's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen with celery and onion until tender.
Debone chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix and work into a stiff ball the flour, water, eggs and salt.
Divide dough and roll thin.
Cut into about 1 inch squares.
Drop into broth.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
A little chicken base can be added, but go light on salt.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix. Set aside 1/2 cup of mix. Mix all other ingredients together; press all but the 1/2 cup of stuffing mix in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour squash mixture over crust; top with remaining stuffing. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 8.

title: australian apple pie
directions: Make dough by sifting 1 cup flour and 1/3 teaspoon of salt into a bowl.
Add shortening with pastry blender until the consistency of coarse sand.
Sprinkle with ice water and toss until balls of dough are formed.
Form into a ball and chill one hour.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and slice in half.
On each cut side, put 1 teaspoon onion, 1/4 teaspoon basil and dash of the seasoned salt to taste.
Cover each with combination of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; dot with a dab of margarine.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until soft and lightly browned.

title: beer batter for perch and pickerel
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand at room temperature for 2 hours before using.
Refrigerate any leftover batter.
It will keep up to 3 weeks.
Dip fish in batter and deep fat fry.

title: white christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs to butter and sugar mixture.
Mix fruit with some flour.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder; mix well and then add flavors, fruits and nuts. Pour into lined tube pan.
Put into cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
After cake is cool, wrap with a cloth soaked in brandy.

title: peach bavarian
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 2/3 cup juice.
Chop peaches into small pieces; set aside.
In a bowl, dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Stir in reserved syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir extract into Cool Whip; gently fold into Jell-O mixture.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into an oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill overnight, unmold, garnish with additional peaches, if desired.

title: cherry carnival
directions: Sift together in bowl the first 3 ingredients.
Add the soft shortening, 1 cup sugar, egg and milk.
Blend in the cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Serve hot with clear red sauce.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar in large mixing bowl; set aside.
Mix beaten egg with orange juice, rind, butter and hot water.
Fold flour mixture into egg mixture until blended.
Do not beat.
Gently fold in cranberries and nuts. Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Test in center with wooden pick.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: lemon asparagus chicken
directions: In skillet in oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove, set aside and spoon off fat.

title: cheese-potato fritters
directions: Blend together mashed potatoes and grated cheese.
Add beaten egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until brown.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour together.
Add butter; blend.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well, then blend for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased pie tin for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chile tostado pie
directions: Grease a 14-inch round pizza pan.
Place tortillas; spread chili evenly over tortillas to edges.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese; continue baking for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with lettuce, remaining cheese, tomato, avocado and olives.
Cut into wedges. Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 3 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shower punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; float cherries, strawberries, limes, oranges or lemons sliced.
Can be frozen and served slushy or serve cold and freeze a portion in a jello mold to float in punch bowl.
Serves 75.

title: favorite mayonnaise cake
directions: Pour 1 cup water over the raisins, nuts and baking soda. Let stand while you prepare the batter. Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar, cocoa, cinnamon and vanilla. Add the flour to this mixture, half at a time, stirring as you go, alternating with the raisin/nut mixture as well. Bake in greased and floured square pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and set on high speed for 15-30 seconds.

title: raisin energy cookies
directions: Chop and cut raisins and apricots coarsely; set aside.
Mix and sift dry milk, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in flour and wheat germ; add oleo or oil and cream in peanut butter. Add brown sugar, then egg and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture, alternating with liquid milk.
Stir in sunflower seeds and oats.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Work in fruits until well mixed.
For jumbo cookies, use heaping tablespoonful onto greased baking sheet and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Let cool on sheet for 5 minutes.

title: unusual frozen cake
directions: Add milk (instead of water) to cake mix, using the same amount as box instructs for water.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Do not bake. Cover pan with foil or tight fitting lid and freezer overnight.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss lightly all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt.
Drain, then place in baking dish. Melt cheese and half of oleo in double boiler.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt remaining oleo and saute crumbs, then put on top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Layer bread and cheese in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together milk, eggs, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Let set overnight.
Before baking, pour 1/4 cup melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
Great for breakfast!

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat oil, add bell pepper, onion, garlic and chilies and saute until tender.

Add broth, chicken, soup, tomatoes, corn, Worcestershire sauce, cumin and chili powder. Season to taste with salt, place tortilla pieces in soup bowl, ladle in soup and top with two tablespoons cheese.
Garnish with avocado or lime slices, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: meatza
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; spread into 9-inch pan. Pour spaghetti sauce over the top. Sprinkle mushrooms and cheese over the sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and refrigerate 4 hours before pouring over vegetables and bacon.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Slice 6 Granny Smith apples and sprinkle with Fruit Fresh.
Dip and eat!

title: marshmallow dressing(for fresh fruit salad)
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and hot water.
Cook until mixture registers 248° or forms thread.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add hot syrup very slowly to egg whites, continuing to beat.
Flavor with vanilla.
When cool, add mayonnaise and orange rind.
(Save a little for topping.)
Serve fruit topped with dressing.

title: hamburger harvest casserole
directions: Combine hamburger, onions, tomatoes, 1 of the seasonings and salt.
Pat into an inch layer in a 3-quart casserole.
Over this, place potatoes, flour, then corn, lima beans and green peppers. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: country breakfast potatoes
directions: In medium skillet, cook green pepper and onion in butter over medium-low heat until tender. Add ham and eggs. Cook until eggs begin to set on bottom and sides. Lift and fold eggs to allow uncooked portion to set. Continue cooking until eggs are soft scrambled.
Season with salt and pepper. Spoon eggs over each potato. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese over each.

title: brownies
directions: In saucepan, add sugar, butter, and water.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup morsels and vanilla until morsels are melted.
Transfer to a medium bowl and cool completely.
Stir in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually stir in flour and soda.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining morsels and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased 9 inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 - 35 minutes.
Done when toothpick comes out clean. Cool and cut into squares.

title: dirty cake
directions: Crush cookies well; set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix together milk, French vanilla pudding and Cool Whip.
Add to cream mixture.
Mix well.
Layer cookies and pudding mixture, end with cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: harriet's rocky mountain brisket
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Rub liquid smoke completely into meat.
Place meat (fat side up) into roasting pan.
Sprinkle dry ingredients on top of beef.
Cover tightly.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake at 325° for 4 hours.
Scrape off seasoning; slice thin and serve.

title: spicy hot cheese cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and shred cheese. Add 1/4 cup into the mix and 1/4 cup sprinkled on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes in hot oven or until firm in the center.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mash banana with sugar; add mayonnaise, salt, flour, soda and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Grease tins.
Makes 1 large tin.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and divide into 24 pieces.
Press into muffin cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave according to instructions on package.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese and cracker crumbs together.
Fold in broccoli.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with a handful of Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: avocado stuffed eggs
directions: Peel shells from eggs; slice in half and gently remove yolks. Mash egg yolks with peeled soft avocados.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon generously into halves of eggs.
Makes 12 delicious eggs.

title: marinade for shish kabob
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool and add meat. Marinate for at least 4 hours.

title: vegetable jambalaya from louisiana
directions: Dice vegetables and saute in butter until butter is melted, then mix everything in baking dish.
Add tomatoes and mix. Sprinkle diced mushrooms on top of mixture.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cook rice and serve vegetable mixture over it.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl. Roll in small balls.
Put in a cool place.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Melt together the paraffin wax and chocolate morsels.
Roll the balls in this mixture.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 9 x 12-inch pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt caramels, milk and pecans.
Spread over cake, then pour rest of cake batter on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: microwave lemon pie filling
directions: Heat
water
2	to
minutes	until simmering.
Blend together
sugar,
cornstarch,
salt and food coloring.
Add to water
slowly, stirring.
Cook, uncovered, 4 minutes, stirring after every
minute.
Beat egg yolks;
add small amount of hot mixture
to
yolks,
stirring well.
Add yolks to hot mixture. Cook,
uncovered, for 1 minute.
Stir well.
Add butter, lemon peel and juice; stir in well.
Cool.
Serve on angel food cake with Cool Whip or as pie filling.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger (or turkey) and onion.
Drain beans. Add all remaining ingredients and bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: baked soy chicken
directions: In large baking pan, stir together everything but chicken. Add chicken and bake in preheated 425° oven, basting occasionally, for 40 minutes or until tender and well browned.
Serve hot or cold.

title: enchilada squares
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Spread beef in bottom of 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Beat together eggs, evaporated milk, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce mix; pour over meat layer. Sprinkle with olives and top with broken up corn chips.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm in center.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.
We usually double recipe in a 9 x 13-inch pan but it takes about 1 hour to firm up in center.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; add soup, parsley, celery, pimento, salt and paprika.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cut-outs
directions: Mix together and roll out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Spread 1 package of crescent rolls on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix center ingredients and spread on top.
Spread over package of crescent rolls on top.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook onions, butter and spices until onions are soft.
In separate bowl stir flour and sour cream together.
Add it to onions and chicken broth.
Cook until thickened.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oleo and water until fluffy.
Sift together, flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture, mix well.
Fold in nuts, chocolate morsels, apples and vanilla.
Spoon into greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 60-70 minutes, until cake tests done.
Cake is tender and moist.
Keeps well.

title: cool watermelon soup(low-fat)
directions: Blend the first five ingredients together.
Chill.
Garnish with mint.

title: creamy corn slaw
directions: Combine vegetables in bowl.
Mix rest of items and pour over salad; chill 1 hour or more.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
Combine the baking mix, milk, and cheddar cheese in a medium bowl.
Mix by hand until well combined.
Spoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 18 -20 min. or until tops of the biscuits begin to brown.
In a small bowl, combine the butter with the garlic powder.
Heat for 30 seconds in the microwave, then brush a light coating over the top of each biscuit immediately after removing them from the oven. Sprinkle a dash of parsley over the top of each biscuit.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: meatballs and brown rice
directions: Combine chuck, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and form into meatballs.
Brown meatballs and drain.
Set aside.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans or 3 round layer pans.
Line bottoms with wax paper.
Pour boiling water on chocolate in small bowl, stirring until chocolate is melted. Cool.
Mix sugar and butter in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in chocolate and vanilla on low speed.
Mix in flour and beat until batter is smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Divide batter among pans.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cherry thing pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Press firmly in 13 x 3-inch cake pan greased or sprayed with Pam pan coating.
Sprinkle pecans down on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Set aside; let cool.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden yellow.
Turn heat off. Add rice to onion-butter mixture until well coated.
Add cheese, wine, chicken stock and salt.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in pan in the order given and spread each layer evenly before adding another. Slice oleo to make a thin layer over the entire cake. Sprinkle pecans over oleo. Bake at 350 about 50 minutes.

title: sweet and saucy dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill.
Very good on crackers or in Lebanon Bologna Roll-Ups.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Add the green tomatoes and sugar together.
Combine all ingredients.
Fill a crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.

title: crowd pleaser potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients together except potatoes.
Add potatoes and stir.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Combine equal parts of water and vinegar; add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Combine the mustard, mayonnaise and eggs.
Add to meat mixture.
Broil until brown, turning once to brown on both sides.

title: menudo
directions: Clean tripe of fat.
Boil in 2 quarts of water for 30 minutes. Add Menudo spice and boil for 30 minutes.
Drain hominy and add to mixture.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
To serve, put onions in a separate bowl, put lemons in a separate bowl.
Sprinkle onion on top of Menudo.
Squeeze lemon in Menudo.
Eat with tortilla. Traditional for Saturday and Sunday morning (hangovers).

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in oblong pan.
No frosting.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use a little milk to rinse soup can. Save a few onion rings to put on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Will not hurt to leave in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix milk, margarine, cocoa and sugar.
Let come to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Place in buttered pan and cool.

title: halibut italian-style
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Arrange halibut steaks in an oven dish large enough to hold them snugly. In a small bowl, whisk wine with lemon juice and oregano. Pour mixture over both sides of fish. Top with basil, parsley and red pepper. Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the apples in a buttered casserole and sprinkle water over them.
Mix together the sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and flour and rub in the butter.
Sprinkle this mixture over the apples.
Cover and bake 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: baked ziti
directions: Brown meat in saucepan, then brown garlic and pepper in oil. Add paste and 1/2 can water; add tomatoes and crush them up with spoon.
Put in salt, pepper, parsley and basil.
Cook for 3/4 hour. Cook ziti, drain and rinse with cold water.
Arrange ziti in baking dish with a layer of sauce and slices of cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put crust in pan. Sift dry ingredients together and stir into eggs; add milk and pumpkin.

title: korean beef strips
directions: Brown the sesame seed lightly over low heat; set aside.
Slice the steak on the diagonal in very thin slices.
Score each slice with an X.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over steak slices.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain meat; reserve marinade.
Broil steak slices as near source of heat as possible for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Turn and sprinkle with sesame seed. Broil 30 seconds longer.
Serve with rice and reserved marinade. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Can be easily reduced to half a recipe.

title: pilau (pilaf)
directions: Cut and season beef or chicken to taste.
Soften peas; boil in water (add bay leaf and thyme for seasoning).
In a deep pot, cook beef or chicken in the margarine or butter until brown, then add cooked peas, rice, coconut cream, carrots and all the other seasonings.
Cover and steam until rice is cooked.
Check periodically; add some hot water if necessary.
When cooked, add chopped sweet pepper.
Serve hot.

title: wendy's chili
directions: Brown beef in a skillet over medium heat.
Drain.
Using a fork, crumble into pea size pieces.
In a large pot, combine beef with the remaining ingredients and bring to a simmer over low heat.
Cook, stirring every 15 minutes, for 2 to 3 hours.

title: hearty corn chowder
directions: Cook the bacon until crisp, remove to paper towels; crumble and set aside.

title: congealed orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple and juice. Put in refrigerator and let congeal to soft state.
Then stir in cheese, mayonnaise and nuts. Return to refrigerator until time to serve.

title: french apple pie
directions: Arrange apples in pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix remaining sugar with flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: teriyaki marinade sauce
directions: Add marinade to meat (chicken, steak, shrimp, etc.).
Cover tightly and refrigerate 6 to 24 hours.
Turn occasionally.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Sift dry ingredients into sugar mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Remove immediately. Cool.
Add frosting.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples thin.
Sift sugar, spice and salt over apples and stir gently until well coated.
Place apples in layers in pie shell, dotting each layer with bits of butter. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Add 2 tablespoons water. Cover with pricked upper crust and bake in hot 425° oven until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix melted margarine, buttermilk, sugar and coconut; add to well beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: walnut cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, coconut, walnuts and pecans; set aside. Cream together the margarine, sugar, buttermilk and eggs.
Mix everything together and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not open oven for the first hour.

title: rice ring chantilly
directions: Combine sugar, salt and gelatin in heavy saucepan.
Stir in milk and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Cool.
Fold in rice and vanilla.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken; fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into lightly oiled 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold.
Serve with sliced sweetened strawberries.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts and dates.
Dip one tablespoon cookie dough and shape into ball.
Top each cookie with cherries cut into fourths.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not store or stack until cold.

title: bacon wrapped chicken livers
directions: Boil livers until blood is out.
Wrap each chicken liver with 1/2 strip bacon and secure with a toothpick; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring this mixture to a boil.
Add livers to this mixture and let marinate at least 2 hours or overnight. Line cookie sheet (with sides) with aluminum foil.
Broil until bacon is browned on one side then turn and brown other side, about 5 minutes each side.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and molasses and blend well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add half of dry mixture to creamed mixture and blend with mixer.
Add remaining half and blend by hand.
Chill dough for several hours.
At this point, you may bake whatever portions of the dough you desire and refrigerate or freeze the remainder.
(Dough keeps covered in the refrigerator for a week.)
To bake, make dough into walnut size balls.
Roll the balls in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour mixed together.
Add one cup of milk, vanilla and melted margarine.
Beat for about 2 minutes then mix in coconut.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Cook about 40 minutes at 350° or until the middle does not shake.

title: no cook lye soap
directions: This was a great spring tonic that was both a treatment and treat!

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry ground chuck; drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning and amount of water it calls for on package.
Mix refried beans with ground chuck.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls; bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans in salted water; drain.
Combine milk, soup and pepper.
Pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining 1/2 can of onions and bake another 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ava's carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots to form a sauce.
Add carrots while still warm.
May be served warm or cold and best if made 24 hours ahead of serving time.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions.
While still warm, pour into the dry cake mix.
Stir.
Spread in cake pan, 10 x 8 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle chips on top; then nuts.
Push into batter with a spoon slightly.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: shiny-top blueberry cobbler
directions: Spread berries in well-greased 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; set aside.
In medium bowl, stir flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk, butter, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt until well blended.
Spoon over berries; spread to edges of baking dish and set aside.
In a small bowl, mix together all remaining ingredients, except water; sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown and glazed.
Serve warm or cool with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, green peppers and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well and boil 15 minutes in 1 pint and 2 parts water.
Drain and boil 20 minutes in 2 quarts vinegar with spices and sugar added.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line a greased 10-inch tube pan with aluminum foil; grease foil well.
Preheat oven to 300°.

title: s.h. kress lemon pudding cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with egg beater just until mixed.
Do not overbeat.
Pour at once into graham cracker crust. Chill one hour.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve on party rye or crackers.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten egg and molasses to dry ingredients.
Mix well, then roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan. Bring to full boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and morsels.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Wait until it sets and cut into desired size pieces.

title: egg bake
directions: Place bread in small greased casserole dish with grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs, half and half, salt, pepper and onion; pour over bread.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: barbecue quickie
directions: Fry hamburger and onion (drain off excess grease).
Add chili sauce, soup and seasonings; blend well.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until soft; mash gently with butter.
Add brown sugar (to your liking); stir.
Bake pie crust 5 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take out of oven; pour in sweet potato mixture and bake 10 to 20 minutes longer.
Sprinkle sugar on top (optional).

title: meat loaf with mashed potatoes
directions: Mix together all items and set aside.
Using instant potatoes, mix up enough for 4 servings.
In a greased 8-inch square pan, put half of the meat mixture, then all of the mashed potatoes and rest of meat mixture on top.
Drizzle catsup on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes before cutting.
Serve with green beans and applesauce with cinnamon.

title: chicken ragout
directions: Dust chicken with flour; brown lightly in oil until no longer pink.
Cut in bite-sized pieces.
Put juices in pot.
Add garlic and mushrooms; cook some.
Add onions; cook some.
Add everything through Madeira.
Make slurry of flour and water; add while stirring.
Add peas; bring to boil.
Cook until peas are tender and sauce is thick.
Add white pepper.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: hot pizza casserole
directions: Prepare pizza crust by directions in a 9 x 13-inch aluminum pan.
Bake until firm.
Cook sausage; drain.
Mix sausage and pizza sauce (from box) and tomatoes.
Layer sauce, sausage and tomatoes; top with cheese.
Repeat until gone.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Let cool and slice.
(Can put pepper seeds, if desired.)

title: hawaiian ribs
directions: Put ribs in large pan.
Mix all and pour over ribs.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°, then 1 hour uncovered at 300°.
Baste often last hour.

title: baked spaghetti dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Cook noodles as directed.
Combine all ingredients, saving small amount of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: hardy cabbage casserole supper
directions: Brown ground meat in large skillet with first 3 ingredients. Add cabbage to mixture and cook until cabbage is slightly soft. Add rest of ingredients. Put into casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Sprinkle cheese on top and serve.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; brown in oil.
Place in baking dish. Combine soup, wine, cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Place on almonds and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: low-fat, sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into pie crusts and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 pies, 12 servings.

title: plantanos panadero (baked bananas)
directions: Peel the bananas and cut in half lengthwise.
Arrange them, cut side up in a lightly greased glass baking dish.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar and a little salt.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
After 15 minutes, spoon the butter over the top and continue baking.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken, then cut into small pieces. Cook spaghetti. Dice up green pepper and onion. Cut cheese into small pieces. Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Sift salt, baking powder and flour together.
Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at at time, beating well after each.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately. Add flavorings.
Pour into well greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or golden brown.

title: creamy cheesy chicken tortellini soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until tender.
Reserve broth. Cool chicken and set aside.
Melt margarine.
Add onions, carrots and celery and saute until tender.
Add water or broth and bring to a boil.
