Add tortellini noodles and cook 12 to 15 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Reduce heat. Add milk, half and half, Cheez Whiz and chicken.
Stir constantly over heat until cheese is melted.
Simmer on low heat until heated through.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Boil and debone the fryer or brown the beef.
Cook the onion and bell pepper in microwave with a little water for 3 minutes. Crumble tostado chips about halfway up a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients. Pour over top of chips and cook at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 45 minutes. Top with slices of American cheese the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt butter, add other ingredients, except fruits.
In pie crust, fill with sliced peaches.
Pour batter over and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(Other fruit can be used.)

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Heat cheese, margarine, chocolate and syrup in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently until melted and smooth.
Gradually add sugar to chocolate mixture.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Smooth surface with spatula.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Cut into squares after firm.
Makes about 3 1/2 pounds.

title: lo-cal fruit and cheese dip
directions: Mix together in a blender.
Chill.
Makes 2 2/3 cups quantity; 50 calories per 1/3 cup dip.

title: whipped cream frosting for large angel food cake
directions: Divide cake into 3 layers and spread frosting on top and sides.
Two envelopes of Dream Whip may be used instead of whipping cream, using 3 cups milk.

title: baked crab dip
directions: Mix in order given.
Place in baking dish.
Top with additional 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: nana's orange sponge cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt 3 times. In a separate bowl, add 1/2 cup sugar to eggs and yolk and beat until thick and lemon colored. Add remaining sugar gradually. Add orange juice, rind and water. Add flour mixture and beat with rotary eggbeater until smooth. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and invert pan until cool.

title: crust for any pie
directions: In a large bowl, with pastry blender or two knives used in a scissor-like fashion, cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle on cold water, a tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with a fork after each addition, until pastry holds together.
Divide dough in half, shape each into a flat ball.
Wrap each in plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour or longer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and add milk.
Stir constantly over direct heat until sauce boils and thickens.
Add corn, salt, onion juice and pimento.
Beat egg yolks and slowly stir into corn mixture.
Cook 2 minutes longer with constant stirring.
Remove from heat and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Turn into buttered baking dish and bake 30 minutes in moderate oven or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and press into 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet (with sides).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: pizza appetizer
directions: Spread the tomato paste on bread.
Mix the ground beef with oregano, basil, onion salt and garlic salt.
Brown mixture. Spread over bread.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on meat.
Top with slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: angel food
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar to stiff peaks.
Sift sugar, salt and flour to blend thoroughly.
Fold dry ingredients into egg whites, then fold in vanilla, taking care not to overmix. Pour into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake in a pan of boiling water at 275° for 1 hour.
Serve with fresh fruit and whipped cream.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone and chop.
Add all other ingredients with chicken and place in baking dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pineapple and add to strawberries, bananas and half of the nuts.
Add to jello mixture. Spread 1/2 of the mixture into a 8 x 12 x 2-inch Pyrex pan and chill for 1 1/2 hours.
Spread sour cream over top of the jello mixture and sprinkle with rest of the nuts.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots until tender in boiling, salted water.
Drain.
Heat soup, vinegar, sugar and oil to boiling. Pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Keeps several weeks.

title: blueberry surprise cake
directions: Combine flour,
cup sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl. Cut
in
butter
until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Beat together eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add to remaining crumb mixture; stir well.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Combine blueberry pie filling or any other fruit of your
choice
(see Note
for suggestions) and optional sugar. Spread over
the
top of cake batter.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/2 cup crumbs.
Bake
oven
for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Makes 16 servings.

title: baked spinach wontons
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook scallions and peppers in oil 1 minute; add next five ingredients and cook 4 minutes more.
Drain. Place 1 tablespoon spinach mixture in centers of wonton wrappers. Brush edges with water.
Fold into triangles; press edges to seal.
Coat with cooking spray.
Bake on greased baking sheet 10 minutes or until golden.
Combine last three ingredients for sauce.
Makes 24 servings.

title: french silk pie
directions: Mix and form into crust.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini according to package directions.
In skillet, saute margarine, green onions and garlic.
Season with salt, pepper, parsley, garlic powder and Tony's seasoning.
Then add shrimp and cook until done, about 7 minutes.
Then add fettucini and half and half.
Cook on low for about 30 minutes or put in crock-pot on low.

title: mint flavored cookies
directions: Dip Ritz crackers in melted chocolate and oil and place on wax paper.

title: sangria slush
directions: Combine juice concentrates and water.
Turn into freezer trays; freeze firm.
Scoop frozen mixture into small bowl.
Fill a larger bowl with ice.
Insert bowl of flush in ice-filled bowl; surround with fruit.
To serve, spoon slush mixture into glass. Pour in red, white or Rose wine.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender; drain off water.
Mix 1/3 cup of margarine, sour cream, salt and pepper into squash and onion.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with topping made with melted margarine and cornbread crumbs. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Regular flour may be used in place of Bisquick. If used, 3/4 teaspoon baking powder is added.

title: fresh peach ice cream(lower in cholesterol and very good)
directions: Peel peaches; mash and combine with 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat together 2 1/2 cups sugar, evaporated milk, eggs and salt in large bowl.
Beat powdered milk and ice water together until light. Combine all ingredients, except 2% milk.
Pour into a one-gallon churn.
Finish filling churn with 2% milk.
Churn until firm.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda and set aside.
Use an electric mixer or a good strong spoon to cream butter.
Add vanilla and sugars and beat or stir until fluffy.
Beat or stir in egg if using an electric mixer.
Beat at low speed, then beat in cocoa, then add milk.
With a big spoon, mix in dry ingredients until blended. Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.

title: margarita punch
directions: Combine the sugar and water in a large saucepan; boil until the sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add the remaining ingredients. Chill.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Pour salt over tomatoes and let set for 3 hours.
Drain well and add other ingredients.
Do not boil, but get real hot and simmer for 10 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: fruit bars
directions: Put 1 cup chopped nuts in bottom of square pan.
Mix in bowl the remaining ingredients, except candied fruits.
Pour over nuts. Mash candied fruit
to the top.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk and pour over butter in pan.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 240° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: golden slush
directions: Mix lemonade, water, pineapple juice, orange juice and sugar. Freeze.
Three to 4 hours before serving, remove from freezer. Just before serving, add frozen mush to cold ginger ale.
Do not add ice to the punch.
Serves 40.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix lemonade and pineapple juice (can be mixed ahead of time).

title: texas hash
directions: Saute beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until onion is tender. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes until rice is tender.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix milk, lemonade and Cool Whip well.
Put in pie crust and set into refrigerator until set.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar until light.
Add flour and chopped nuts.
Cream with spoon until mixture forms crumbs.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Set pan on rack to cool.

title: upside-down peach cobbler
directions: Pour batter over butter and fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veggie salad
directions: Combine corn, peas, green beans, onions, celery, green pepper, and pimentos in bowl.
Toss to mix.
Combine oil, sugar and vinegar in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for several minutes.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Chill overnight to several days, stirring once each day.
Season with salt and pepper just before serving.
Makes 24 servings.

title: knox blox
directions: In medium bowl, combine Knox unflavored gelatine and fruit flavored gelatin. Add boiling water and stir until gelatins are completely dissolved.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch baking pan. Chill until firm.

title: easy pineapple cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour crushed pineapple into pan. Spread cherry pie filling into pan over pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over cherry pie filling. Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Top with small pieces of margarine. Bake for 1 hour.

title: tangy cauliflower
directions: Wrap loosely with plastic wrap, rinsed and trimmed cauliflower.
Microwave 6 to 10 minutes on High, depending on size.

title: boston cookies
directions: Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In medium bowl, cream butter and gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Beat in egg.
Thoroughly blend in flour mixture. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Add salt and set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, 1 stick melted oleo and grated cheese; mix well.
Mix with squash.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Pour 1/2 stick melted oleo over top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until very hot and bubbly throughout.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oriental rice salad
directions: *Use turkey, shrimp, tuna, beef, etc.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix until smooth and creamy.
Pour into 2 small graham cracker crusts.
For eye appeal, top with a few peanut butter chips.

title: layer sandwich loaf
directions: Cut off crusts of breads.
Slice breads lengthwise into 5 layers.
Place bottom layers end to end.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Layer half of ravioli, 1 1/4 cups of spaghetti sauce, 1 cup of cottage cheese and 2 cups of Mozzarella.
Repeat layering.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fortified macaroni and cheese
directions: Make a white sauce by melting 2 tablespoons butter or oil in saucepan.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour to make a paste.
Add 1 cup milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Add frozen vegetables.
Simmer and stir 10 minutes over medium heat.
Add cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour into blender until smooth.
Pour over cooked macaroni.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In a small bowl, mix 1 teaspoon sugar, salt, yeast, 1/2 cup cold water and eggs.
Mix with mixer and set aside.

title: spicy rice with black-eyed peas
directions: Cook peas as directed on package using 10-inch nonstick skillet; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; break up tomatoes. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until liquid is almost absorbed.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together apples, sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and add to the first mixture. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Boil butter, cocoa and water; pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost with Fudge Frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese out in mixing bowl to soften an hour or so before mixing.
Add onion, pepper and squeezed dry pineapple. Mix together well by hand.
Have chopped pecans spread out on wax paper.
Separate sour cream mixture into balls.
Roll in pecans until completely coated.
Wrap ball in aluminum foil, store in refrigerator for a day before serving.
Goes with Sociables crackers best.

title: chicken mushroom risotto
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon margarine cook cut up chicken, stirring often.
Remove and set aside.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same pan in remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine cook rice, carrot and onion until rice is browned, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth, soup and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in peas and reserved chicken.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all other ingredients and gently mix with potatoes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake uncovered in preheated 350 degree oven for 35 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Generously grease bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread pecans and coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over coconut-pecan mixture.
In separate saucepan, melt butter and cream cheese until creamy.
Stir in sugar until smooth.
Pour over cake mix.
(This will look funny.) Use entire mixture; try to get close to sides.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered dish. Bake in a 350° oven until set around edges, then stir.
Continue cooking until it is set in center.
You may add a dash of cinnamon or nutmeg, if you like.
Set a pan of hot water on oven rack below pudding while baking.

title: smothered steak
directions: Flour steak and brown in a small amount of fat.
Remove steak to casserole dish.
Brown flour in grease.
Add soups and liquid. Pour over steak.
Bake at 300° for approximately 3 hours or until very tender.

title: plum bread
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and marshmallows.
Spread mixture in a pizza pan.
Top with cherries and coconut; melt white chocolate and drizzle over top.
Let set up before cutting and serving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions for 4 hours in salt and enough water to cover; drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and turmeric. Simmer until cucumbers are a bright yellow.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
This recipe makes 5 pints.

title: mike's mom's apple pie
directions: Blend together and place in uncooked pie crust. Top with strips of uncooked pie crust. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Dot with 1/4 stick oleo, cut in pieces. Bake at 350° until top is lightly browned.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix together well.
Add Mozzarella cheese after beating together.
Fill cooked manicotti shells.
Place in pan and cover with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar and margarine; mix well.
With lightly buttered hands, roll into balls.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: In mixing bowl, pour water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes. Add sugars and butter, stirring until butter melts.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift flour, soda, cocoa and salt together.
Add to batter.
Mix well.
Stir in half the chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of cake with walnuts and remaining chips.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
May be served plain, iced, with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Mix in eggs and bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into banana mixture.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well and turn into greased loaf pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before serving.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail to boiling. Add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Add Cool Whip to buttermilk and fold into jello mixture. Fold in diced bananas.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set.
(Low-cal.)

title: guacamole tomato salad
directions: Scoop out avocados and tomatoes, turning upside down to drain. Cut avocado meat into 1/2-inch cubes and sprinkle with lemon or lime juice. Dice tomato pulp into 1/4-inch cubes and add
to avocado.
Chill.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice off top of pepper, scoop out seeds and white membrane. Blanche peppers in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes until slightly tender; drain well.
Halved peppers can also be used with blanching directions.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in skillet.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay a tomato slice on each chop; add green pepper ring.
Fill with chopped onions.
Top chops with soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: beth's hot dog sticks
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan.
Quarter buns lengthwise (4 long sticks).
Dip top edge in bowl of butter and lay on cookie sheet, butter side up.
Sprinkle buttered edge with seasonings.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 250°.
Keep in covered container.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine milk or cream with vinegar.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Add the soured milk and blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° to 400° about 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: unbaked frozen orange juice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; make into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Set on waxed paper; cookies will set up after some time.

title: gooey butterscoth bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cool.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Toss in dry ingredients; add nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 9x13 inch pan.
Cover with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: cookie brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.

title: butterscotch icebox torte
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press down and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas.
Stir to blend.
Spread 1/8 inch of mixture on flat tortilla.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Chill.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Stir in corn, then put in beaten eggs. Next, add salt and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Peel, pare and cut thin apples.
Mix with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon; toss in bowl until apples are covered. Set aside.
Put all other ingredients in mixer bowl and blend at low speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Grease tube pan and fill alternately layers of batter and apple mixture (3 layers batter; 2 of apples, begin with batter). Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool.
Turn out on plate.

title: shrimp dip (or mold)
directions: Grind together the cooked shrimp and ham.
Mix this combination with cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Line a mold with dampened cheesecloth.
Place mixture in mold; let stand overnight.
Unmold onto a tray.
Garnish to suit the season or occasion.
Serves 15 or more.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in casserole and top with chicken.
Combine salad dressing, curry powder and soup; pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and croutons and dab with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Brown bread crumbs in butter.
Pour mix into large casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight if possible.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain well. In a large saucepan, combine beef and all remaining ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender. Serve with hot corn bread. Better on the second day.

title: best and easiest cobbler
directions: Mix the fingers or fork until crumbly.
Prepare any fruit in bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan (peaches, apricots, apples, rhubarb, etc.).
Put crumbly mix over top.
Melt 1 cube butter or margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup with 1 soup can of water. Combine rice, hamburger, onion, seasonings and 4 tablespoons soup; mix well.
Form into balls.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with remaining soup.
Bake, covered at 350°, for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Remove the cover for the remaining 15 minutes of baking.
Yields 5 servings.

title: pesto genovese
directions: Blend basil, olive oil, pine nuts, garlic and salt in blender first, then add remainder of ingredients.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix the above ingredients well. Pour into a 9 X 13 inch pan or a loaf pan and bake at 350° F. for 1 hour or until done.
Cover with 1 can of tomato sauce for the last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: amanda's no-bake cookies(kid recipe)
directions: Mix together cocoa, sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and remove from stove.
Add the peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well and drop on waxed paper by teaspoon. These are ready to eat when you are finished dropping them.

title: garden fresh pasta
directions: Cook pasta to desired texture as directed on package.
Drain. Keep warm.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add green onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Add pasta, tomato, chicken broth and mustard.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Remove from heat.
Add arugula and Parmesan cheese.
Toss.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, when well mixed, add enough milk to it until you can mold into cookies.
Then roll in poppy seed. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions until tender in a large kettle.
Add ground beef and sausage. Stir often until meat is done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Divide finished product into 4 equal parts.
Serve 1 part with spaghetti and freeze the remaining 3 parts for another time.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat Cool Whip and milk together until smooth.
Add lemonade and beat well.
Pour in pie shells.
Can refrigerate or freeze for later use.

title: old fashion cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Place crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over it.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: diet (sugar-free) lemon pie
directions: Let Jell-O gel slightly.
Add yogurt and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: low country boil
directions: Put water in pot.
Start up a gas cooker and boil potatoes and onions.
Cook until potatoes are half done.
Add sausage and cook 4 minutes.
Add corn and cook 6 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until the shrimp turn a pink color.
Drain and serve.

title: banana split pie
directions: Press in bottom of pan.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
(I have also used a 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: spooky punch
directions: Combine cider and orange juice in pitcher.
Refrigerate until serving time.
In a punch bowl, place one tray of ice cubes or an ice mold.
Pour cider-orange mixture over ice.
Stir in ginger ale.
Add a few sprigs of mint if desired to garnish.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: In a heavily buttered baking dish (9 x 13-inch), spread out the cooked apples.
Sprinkle cake mix over the apples.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: strawberry candies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Rub hands in butter and form mixture into about 75 balls.
Start forming balls into strawberry shapes as you roll them in red sugar.
Put a plastic leaf in each one and freeze.
Allow to defrost 10 minutes before serving. After defrosting they keep well in refrigerator.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix flour and margarine; press in the bottom of a square pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: dorothy shellenbergers green bean casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter.
Add flour; cook until smooth and cream slowly, then add cheese and seasoning.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: sirloin chowder
directions: Brown meat and onion in deep kettle, stirring.
Drain well. Add tomatoes, beef broth, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper. Cook while preparing carrots and celery, then add carrots, celery and lima beans and continue cooking 45 minutes.
Cook slowly, covered.
If too thick, add 1 to 2 cups of water or more beef broth.
After 45 minutes, add sugar and stir well.
Add corn; cover and turn the heat off.
The corn will cook from the heat of the soup.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange (unbaked) rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Cook butter and cinnamon until it bubbles.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover tightly with foil and let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ritz cracker and peanut butter cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Stick toothpick in middle hole of crackers.
Melt almond bark in microwave.
Dip crackers in bark and place on waxed paper or foil until chocolate is hard.
One package almond bark makes 40 cookies.

title: sloppy joe tartlets
directions: Allow both crust pouches to stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°.
Unfold each crust.
Press out fold lines.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of flour over each crust.
Place crust, flour side down, on cutting board or pastry cloth.

title: baked stuffed eggs
directions: Cook the minced onion in the butter a few minutes.
Mix with parsley, mustard, lemon juice and a little salt and pepper.
Cut eggs in half, remove the yolks and mash.
Mix with the onion, seasonings and ham.
Add a little more lemon juice if needed for smoothness.
Fill the white halves and arrange them in a baking dish.
Pour the white sauce over them and sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Heat in moderate oven (350°) until the top is browned. Serves 4 to 6.
Real good and filling, too.

title: mer's pepper steak
directions: Cut steak and peppers into bite size pieces.
Cut onion into wedges.
Cook onion in shortening until transparent.
Set aside and cook peppers until tender; set aside.
Brown steak and add ketchup and cornstarch, dissolved in water.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce and cook until sauce thickens. Add peppers and onion minutes before serving.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.

title: tropical beans
directions: Combine in 1 1/4-quart or larger casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa, and cola to boiling; pour over flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly and add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla, and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Place in a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Layer in order in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix
in
order the sugar, egg, margarine, orange juice, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Grease only the bottom of	the loaf pan.
Once all ingredients are together, then add bananas and
nuts
(optional).
Bake
at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn oven
down to 350° and cook for another 15 minutes. Turn
oven off
for
the
next
minutes, leaving the door closed.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Thoroughly cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Add flour, salt and buttermilk, mixing until smooth.

title: chewy butter cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Pack into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: hunter's lodge one dish meal
directions: Brown venison, onion and celery in butter.
Mix together and add rice, canned soups, mushrooms, soy sauce and seasonings. Place in casserole.
Add peas and water.
Bake in moderate oven until rice and meat are tender.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Slice each shrimp lengthwise, deep enough to form cavity for stuffing.
Mix all ingredients except crabmeat and crumbs.
Pour over crabmeat that has been mixed. Fill cavities of shrimp with crabmeat and deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill and serve.

title: snowball cake
directions: Combine gelatin, boiling water, sugar, salt, juice and pineapple.
Refrigerate to set.
Fold in 2 packages whipped Dream Whip.
Line 10-inch round mixing bowl with wax paper.
Add pineapple mixture alternately with pieces.
Let stand for at least 4 hours in refrigerator.
Unmold on plate; top with 2 packages Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Decorate with maraschino cherries and citron for Christmas.
Yields 12 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl with mixer.
Can be used immediately or refrigerated for up to five days, covered.
Roll out on floured surface and cut biscuits 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.
Cook at 425° for about 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: fruit jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, strawberries, bananas and blueberries, not sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of the jello mixture into a serving dish.
Leave this 1/2 in the refrigerator until it hardens.
Leave the other 1/2 at room temperature.
After the first half hardens, spread the sour cream over it and then spread the other half of the jello on top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mom's bestest pancakes ever
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, egg, vegetable oil and sugar; add enough milk to make a creamy smooth batter. Heat pancake skillet on medium heat. Flip when bubbles pop and brown other side. Keep warm in pancake warmer until ready to serve. Serve with crisp bacon and scrambled eggs.

title: uncle sam's cranberry sauce
directions: Cook cranberries as directed on package.
When done, let them cool.
Add to cooled berries, cinnamon, dry mustard, mace and dash of salt.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup of pineapple juice.
Mix cranberries, pineapple, 4 ounces wine and gelatine.
Chill.

title: 8 can soup
directions: Heat together in crock-pot and enjoy.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, cooking oil and eggs; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Blend in the milk, pumpkin and pecans.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Cool and frost.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion; mix with remaining ingredients. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until top is light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crackers, margarine and poppy seed. Mix soup, sour cream and broth in separate bowl.
Layer in large baking dish in this order:
soup mix, chicken, cracker mix. Repeat, ending with crackers. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle parmesan
directions: In 3-quart saucepan combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper; add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: "super bowl" chip dip
directions: Melt together cheeses.
Add chili; heat and serve warm with tortillas.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, bacon and onion.
Combine remaining ingredient.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo.
Add pecans and coconut.
Mix well. Roll into small balls and stick toothpicks in each ball; chill. Melt the chocolate and paraffin in pan over boiling water.
Dip candy in this mixture and refrigerate again.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Boil chicken until tender.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Layer broccoli, chicken and soup in casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and
soda.
Add
milk and egg; beat well. Add oil and remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 350° not less than 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. When cool, frost with any white frosting.

title: ham casserole
directions: Place chunked ham and sliced potatoes in buttered casserole. Top with cream and shredded cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef and onion cheese ball
directions: Mix well all ingredients, but the nuts.
Form into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pear juice.
Add 1 cup water and let set.
Beat pears and cheese.
Add to jello and fold in whipped cream.

title: chilled peach soup
directions: Mix together cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water; set aside. Place water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon in saucepan; bring to boil. Whisk in cornstarch mixture, stirring constantly. Return to boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Strain and cool to room temperature. Whisk in wine and refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Puree peaches in a food processor or blender; stir into the cold syrup. Stir in the cream; cover and refrigerate. Spoon into wine or parfait glasses.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Add jello and lemon juice.
Blend well.
Fold into whipped Milnot. Mix crumbs and butter together and put 2/3 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in filling and put rest of crumbs on top.
Chill several hours or overnight.
This also freezes well.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soak yeast in water in a large bowl. Add salt and sugar; mix in flour to soft and smooth dough forms. Do not let rise. Cut into pieces.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over carrots.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: gingerbread(meat frying may be used)
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, fat and egg.
Add the milk and then the flour, sifted with all other dry ingredients.
Beat hard.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Cook until thick; may add pimento if desired.
Put in buns and put in oven and warm up.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Combine oats, flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: molasses cookies(christmas cookies for the whole family)
directions: Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and spices; sift over oats. Add raisins and mix.
Stir together cooking oil, molasses, milk and egg.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Drop on oiled pans and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: holiday chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain the cherries well and pat dry.
Combine the butter, evaporated milk and vanilla in a mixing bowl and beat until blended.
Add confectioners sugar and mix until smooth.
Divide mixture into small portions and spread around each cherry, enclosing completely.
Place on waxed paper covered trays and chill until firm.
Melt the chocolate over hot water.
Dip each covered cherry in the chocolate to cover completely while holding stem.
Place on waxed paper.
Let stand until chocolate is firm. Store in an airtight container.
Yield: 20-25 cherries.

title: chocolate chip cookies -- large batch
directions: Cream first four ingredients and then add the balance and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: verna's jello salad(1964 cookbook)
directions: Dissolve the jello
in the hot water-fruit juice combination. Add the rest
of
the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil, then cool.
Add rest of ingredients and freeze.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake according to package instructions.
Add 3 tablespoons creme de menthe to mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Cool.
Spread fudge frosting onto cooled cake.
Add 2 tablespoons creme de menthe extract to whipped topping and mix well.
Spread whipped cream mixture over fudge frosting.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours before cutting.
Serves 16.

title: chicken over rice
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture. Cover with foil or lid. Bake 1 hr 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: strawberry sour cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash and halve berries.	Place evenly in unbaked shell.
Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Add sour cream and stir well.
Pour mixture over berries and spread evenly. Sprinkle reserved sugar over top.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake another 30 minutes or until crust is light golden brown.

title: fruited turkey salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper in mixing bowl. Add turkey, almonds and celery; toss.
Stir grapes into salad just before serving.
Serve on salad greens.

title: grecian lemon cake
directions: Mix 1st five ingredients on low speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker or oven
at 325° until tender.
Usually takes about 2 hours.

title: jalapeno rice dish
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions for 4 cups cooked rice (shorten cooking time).
In meantime, slice thinly and cut into finger-length slices the Jack cheese.
Chop peppers coarsely and add to sour cream.
Butter large casserole and add 1/3 of rice.
Next, layer 1/2 of Jack cheese and 1/2 of peppers and sour cream mixture.
Continue to layer and end with rice.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Return to oven for another 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sugar-free icebox pie
directions: Mix until thick.
Add 3/4 (8 ounce) carton of fat-free Cool Whip.
Pour into a reduced fat graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add pecans. Divide into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Check after 40 minutes frequently.
Wait until golden brown and let set but not "too" brown.
May serve with unsweetened whipped cream. Great for holidays.

title: quick easy rolls
directions: Mix well.
Put into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Butter tops as soon as you take from oven.
Serve hot.

title: dip
directions: Layer, starting with first ingredient.
Serve with chips.

title: chili-cheesy moose steak
directions: Cut moose into serving sized pieces.
Combine flour, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Pound into meat on both sides.
Brown well in hot shortening.
Remove from pan and brown onions in drippings.
Spoon onions into large casserole and arrange steak pieces on top, then undrained tomatoes.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours (or until meat is tender) at 350° (175° C).
Sprinkle with grated cheese and heat 5 minutes longer to melt cheese.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into cupcake liners (I like the little 1 1/2-inch diameter liners), about 2/3 full.
Bake 40 minutes at 300° (will not be brown, only raise up).
Take out of oven and let cool 10 minutes.
A slight indention will form in center.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift flour with soda.
Add 2 cups flour, then milk.
Add last cup flour and sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or 1 Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: alaskan fruit salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of the lemonade.
In medium saucepan, combine the remaining lemonade, the pudding mix and the softened gelatin.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Chill until partially set.
Whip cream. Fold in oranges, pineapple and cherries.
Chill until mixture mounds; turn into mold.
Chill until firm, 4 to 5 hours or overnight (overnight is best).
Unmold and garnish with additional fruit, if desired.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo together.
Mix together pecans, sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla and add to chocolate mixture.
Bake in muffin tins at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Coat steak with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in oil.
Place in baking dish and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: biscotti
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir well.	Stir together salt, baking powder and flour.
Fold into wet mixture. Add nuts.
Shape into 2 logs on lined cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool 15 minutes.
Slice into 1/2 inch thick pieces.
Place on cookie sheet and cook on each side for 10 minutes at 325°.
Can be dipped into melted chocolate.

title: stuffed green pepper
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise and remove seeds and ribs. Drop peppers into boiling water; turn off and set aside for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in beef and saute until evenly browned.
Drain tomatoes, combining juice with V-8 juice and stir into skillet along with remaining ingredients except juices and Parmesan cheese.
Cool slightly.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture and set close together in greased baking dish.
Pour tomato juice around them and sprinkle each with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Add shortening and sugar to the cup of boiling water and let dissolve over low heat.
Cool.
Dissolve salt and yeast in the cold water.
Combine these mixtures and add well beaten eggs and flour.
Mix thoroughly and keep in covered container in refrigerator; let rise 2 hours before baking 20 minutes in hot oven (425° to 450°).

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 75 sausage balls.
To reheat, preheat oven to 300° and warm for about 6 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread and roll out into a rectangle.
Beat the egg and brush on bread dough.
Put a layer of pepperoni and cheese down the middle of dough lengthwise.
Fold over and put another layer of cheese and pepperoni.
Fold over the other way and seal tightly.
Brush remaining egg over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple bread(2 loaves)
directions: Bake at 350° about 3/4 hour, longer if making one large loaf instead of two.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar together in a medium bowl.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in the cornmeal, lemon zest and lemon juice.
Pour the mixture into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: walton's mountain coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put nuts on bottom.
Add rolls (break into individual rolls and place around pan).
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put brown sugar and butter in a pan and heat until sugar melts.
Pour over frozen rolls.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 35 minutes.
Invert immediately.
Pull rolls apart and enjoy!

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to directions on box for a sheet cake (13 x 9 x 2-inch pan) and cool.
Make pudding according to directions on box and chill.
Spread drained pineapple on cooled cake.
Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Add pudding and beat until creamy and thick.
Spread mixture on cake over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over this mixture.
Top with nuts and/or cherries.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix until smooth. Fill a greased and floured baking pan or 2 layer pans no more than 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly touched near center.

title: wesson oil pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9-inch pie pan with a fork.
When completely mixed, shape crust to pie pan.
For a top crusted pie, save 1/4 of crust and roll out between wax paper.
Lay on top of pie filling and peel off the waxed paper.
Bake according to pie recipe being made.

title: super salt substitute
directions: Mix in blender.
Store in a jar with added rice to prevent caking.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar together in a saucepan.
Stir until mixture is smooth and sugar is not too grainy.
Cool just a little and add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and nuts to butter mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8 x 8-inch) pans.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: pie crust - double(2 pies or 1 two crust pie)
directions: Mix flour and salt with a fork.
Make a well in the middle. Put oil and water into a beater and pour in the well.
Mix with a fork, then make two balls to roll out.

title: crock-pot round steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into cubes.
Place in crock-pot.
In a small bowl, mix the soups and water.
Pour over steak.
Cover and cook on low for about 6 hours.

title: "the big 3" peanut butter cookie
directions: Mix together.
Do not put anything else in this.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend and add garlic.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, Eagle Brand milk and lime juice together.
Add two drops green food coloring, if desired.
Pour into graham cracker crumb crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill. Spread whipped whipping cream on top.
Garnish with lime slices. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook ground beef until it loses red color.
Remove from heat. Add catsup and spices.
Add cheese.
Add egg and bread crumbs; mix well.

title: vinegar beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Add vinegar and mix.
Put on stove in heavy pan and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over cubed beets and add 1 tablespoon butter.
Let stand on back of stove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: campers mix
directions: Melt butter in large frypan over medium heat.
Add sliced potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle Adolph's tenderizer over all and mix well until browned.
Add sliced green beans and black pepper and mix until hot.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add cherry juice and cook until sauce thickens, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice, sugar and almond extract. Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix milk, flour, egg, salt and pepper well.
Dip chicken in milk mixture (drain excess liquid); roll in corn flake crumbs. Place in a greased baking dish.
Chip margarine over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Do not turn chicken while baking.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan at 350°.
Mix the flour, milk and sugar in bowl.
Pour over melted butter.
Drain peaches, then pour over mixture.
Bake until golden brown on top.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients using only one cup of pecans.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: uncle don's hawaiian meatballs
directions: Part 1:
Mix thoroughly the beef or turkey, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs; keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: bishop cake
directions: Mix and cook 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Boil the raisins in the water until water is about gone.
Add the soda. Set aside.

title: watercress salad
directions: Wash, drain and cut watercress into 2 inch lengths.
Mix together the next 7 ingredients.
Pour over the watercress, then sprinkle with sesame seed.
Chill for 1 hour but serve at room temperature.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Melt shortening in saucepan.
Remove and add honey and remaining 4 1/2 cups water. Add the whole wheat flour, instant potatoes, dry milk and salt to saucepan.
Beat until smooth.
Add yeast and beat well.
With a wooden spoon, add enough white flour to make dough leave sides of bowl.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and divide into 3 loaves.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: cookandies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a heavy boil and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spoon onto waxed paper.
Cool several hours.
Yield: approximately 3 dozen.

title: banana fruit nut loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in regular size bread pan.

title: lois moore's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over butter.
Cover with top to melt butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Must be lukewarm before adding yeast.
Add flour.
Let rise.
Oil top and refrigerate.

title: basic cream pie filling
directions: In large heavy saucepan, heat 4 cups of the milk with vanilla and lemon extract.
In meantime, heat remaining ingredients together in a bowl and add to the heated milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring with a wooden spoon until it thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Lay waxed paper or plastic wrap directly over pudding while it cools.
Whip a time or two with hand beater or wire whisk as it is cooling.
Makes enough for 2 pies.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Chop onion; put on top and underneath brisket in baking pan. Shake liquid smoke; pour small bottle over brisket, letting it run underneath.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain.
Add 1/2 bottle Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle with Creole seasoning.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
You can add barbecue sauce the last hour and uncover.

title: finnish ribbon cakes(cookies)
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and lemon peel.
In another bowl, stir together flour and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Shape dough into ropes about 3/4-inch in diameter and as long as baking sheet.
Place on baking sheet 2-inches apart. Press long groove down the center of each rope.
Bake cookies at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove cookies from oven and spoon jam into grooves.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until cookies are firm.
While cookies are hot, drizzle them with powdered sugar mixture, then cut at 45° angle into 1-inch length.
Let cool briefly on bake sheet, then place on racks.
Let cool completely.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and boil in double boiler until thick; set aside.
Add all but Dream Whip to first mixture; mix thoroughly.
After cold, add Dream Whip all through.
Keep refrigerated.

title: revised baked beans(lo-fat)
directions: Saute Canadian bacon in a large skillet until slightly browned.

Add ground beef and onion; cook until beef is fully browned and onion is translucent. Drain off the fat and pour mixture into a 3 or 4-quart baking dish. Stir all remaining ingredients into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil amount of potatoes you need for amount of people you are serving. Fry bacon in a skillet until crisp. Remove bacon strips from the pan. Saut onion in bacon drippings until limp; then add flour, then sugar, salt, pepper, water and vinegar. Boil 2 minutes. Add crumbled bacon and potatoes to the seasoned sauce. Heat slowly.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat brown sugar, butter or margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy. Gradually blend in flour mixture alternately with water.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until browned and no longer wet in center.

title: taco popcorn crunch
directions: In a large baking pan combine 3 quarts popped popcorn (without salt), Rice Chex and walnuts.
Drizzle with taco seasoning mix and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over popcorn.
Toss until combined.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Kids really love this.

title: cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish or spray with Pam.
Bring salted water to boil.
Slowly add grits, stirring constantly.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and cook 3 to 5 minutes, until thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add garlic cheese (which has been sliced to melt faster) and margarine.
Stir until both are melted.

title: short ribs with barbecue sauce
directions: Season short ribs with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned, about 30 minutes.
Pour off any accumulated fat in pan. Cool ribs. Set aside.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all together; spread on tortillas.
Roll up.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and serve.
May also be heated until cheese melts.

title: cajun shrimp gumbo
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large crock-pot (recipe may be cut in half for smaller crock-pot).
Do not drain tomatoes or vegetables.
Stir.
Heat as follows:
6 hours on low and then 3 hours on high.
The longer it simmers the better.
This soup is great served with corn muffins or crackers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cook sweet pato pumpkin; drain off all water.
Mash real good. Mix all together; put in pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done.
Do not overcook.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and put back in skillet.
Add brown gravy mix and water.
Cook together for about 10 minutes, moist but not too soupy.
Make up 4 servings instant mashed potatoes per instructions (I use Idaho).
Put ground beef mixture in small casserole dish.
Layer mashed potatoes.
Add grated cheese to top. Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: quick apple kuchen
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread apples on dough.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat all together and pour in chocolate graham cracker pie shell.
Drizzle hard shell chocolate syrup over pie.

title: scalloped potatoes in cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and seasoning and stir smooth.
Slowly add the hot milk, stirring constantly.
When it thickens, melt the grated cheese in the sauce.
Into a buttered casserole, put layers of sliced potatoes, onion and cheese sauce, repeating until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle parsley flakes on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn lasagna
directions: Brown beef and season with salt and pepper.
Prepare the lasagna noodles.
Mix together the corn, soup and cream cheese. Add the ground beef. Layer the noodles and meat mixture in a baking dish.
Top with the Mozzarella cheese; bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add egg and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together; sprinkle over crushed Butterfinger bars and combine with wet ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes for chewy cookies; 11 1/2 to 12 minutes for crunchy cookies.
May double or triple recipe.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mixed fruit, saving liquid.
Drain oranges.
Slice bananas and toss with lemon juice to prevent turning brown.
Mix pudding, using fruit juices instead of milk. Add Tang.
Combine fruits and pudding mixture.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape in balls the size of a walnut.
Place in flat pan, only one layer per pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Blend mushroom soup and water and pour over chicken. Sprinkle on dry soup mix.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: laverne's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add them to the creamed mixture with milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.
Add 1/2 cup nuts last (flour them), if desired.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and warm water; put in dark for 5 minutes. Mix 2 cups boiling water, butter, sugar, 1 tablespoon salt, 2 well beaten eggs and flour.
Add this mixture and yeast mixture together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with towel.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients.
Dip apple slices and enjoy.

title: pickled peppers(hot or sweet)
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut lengthwise into quarters (I leave hot peppers whole).
Place peppers in large glass or ceramic bowl (I use large crock).
In large kettle, combine cooking, canning, and pickling salt and 5 cups water.
Heat until salt dissolves.
Cool salt water, then pour over peppers.
Let stand overnight or for 12 to 14 hours.
Drain.
(I usually leave in salt water 8 hours.) Pack into hot sterilized pint jars.
In 3 quart saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, 1 cup water and garlic.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Pour over peppers in jars, filling to 1/4-inch from top.
Remove air bubbles.
Wipe rims of jars.
Heat flat metal lids (one at a time) for 30 seconds in boiling water.
Remove and place on jars. Screw on rings.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 4 long rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove Saran Wrap and lay on a rack in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Turn sausage rolls once during baking.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: fried rice
directions: Dice all meat in small pieces. In large skillet, braise pork and steak, then add spam and onion.
Cook about 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add already scrambled eggs.
In separate boiler, cook 1 cup of rice (I use water maid).
Let stand after cooking for 20-25 minutes.
Add rice to mixture in skillet, mix in soy sauce and stir real good.

title: frozen margaritas
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart container that you can freeze.
Before serving, stir up the frozen mixture into a slush. Scoop into a glass and serve with a slice of lime.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, butter, flour, salt and pecans. Pour into pie shell that has been baked for a few minutes (long enough to dry out).
Then bake at 350° for about an hour or until middle is firm.

title: crunchy celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of water, approximately 5 minutes. (The celery should still be crunchy.)
Drain and combine with chestnuts, soup and seasonings.
Grease a two quart casserole. Place first mixture into casserole and top with combined breadcrumbs, almonds and butter.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin with water; stir until dissolved.
Fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts. Spoon half of mixture into baking dish or mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over set mixture.
Spoon rest of mixture on top.
Chill until set.

title: low-fat fried potatoes
directions: Spray cast-iron skillet with Pam.
Add sliced potatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat until slightly browned.
Turn.
Add 1/4 cup cold water.
Keep adding water and turning as needed to prevent sticking.
Cook until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix and boil first eight ingredients.
Boil slowly for 5 minutes.
Add flour, soda, salt and walnuts.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for at least 1 1/4 hours.

title: mommy's "famous" potatoes
directions: Clean and dice potatoes.
Pour enough olive oil to coat.
Use seasoning to taste.
Mix together.
Bake on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam at 400° for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy turkey soup
directions: In 4 quart saucepan, combine all ingredients except macaroni. Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally until mixture comes to a full boil (10 to 15 minutes). Reduce heat to medium, add macaroni. Cover. Cook, stirring occasionally until macaroni is tender (12 to 15 minutes).

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet until beef is done. Drain. Stir in soup, thyme and salt. Cook a few more minutes.
Mix potatoes according to package directions or mash your own. Pour beef mixture into small casserole dish.
Spread potatoes on top. Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until potatoes are brown.

title: sesame topped broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli in 2-inch pieces.
In 10-inch skillet over high heat, heat butter, soy sauce and water to boiling.
Stir in broccoli.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook approximately 7 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms in butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until onions are translucent.
Stir in chicken, tomato puree, wine, parsley, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and cover.
Cook 2 minutes more.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Return to heat, add next six ingredients and cook for 1 minute.
Stir into beans and bake on 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg with mixer.
Pat dough into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and lemon extract.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cut in squares when completely cool.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Melt margarine and combine all ingredients. Place in large (9 x 13) baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until brown on top.

title: waldorf red velvet cake
directions: A.
Add 1 cup milk to 5 tablespoons flour in a kettle and cook until thick, stirring.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well; add last 3 ingredients.
Mix together and let stand overnight.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.
These cookies may be kept in refrigerator or frozen indefinitely.

title: onion (vidalia) casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onions.
Add cooked rice, parsley, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add Swiss cheese and cream. Pour into
a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mott's quick chunky apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Prepare pie crusts according to package directions using 2 jars Mott's chunky applesauce as filling. Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired. Cut a few vents for steam to escape. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 25 to 30 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.
For best results, cool completely before serving.
Enjoy.

title: salsa
directions: Peel and dice the tomatoes. Dice the green pepper. Dice the onion. Dice the pepper and garlic. Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix all ingredients. Chill for 2 hours.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Brush bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with oil.
Mix Bisquick, Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning, paprika and pepper; coat chicken.
Arrange skin side down.
Bake 45 minutes.
Turn chicken. Divide chili sauce among chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until melted, about 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add cooled meat last.
Use favorite taco sauce to taste.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover with topping (recipe follows).

title: nasturtium zinger spread
directions: Finely chop the nasturtium, onions and mushrooms.
Mix it well with either mayonnaise or cream cheese and spread it on toast.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in small bowl; set aside (except sugar). Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas until mixed, then add buttermilk, dry ingredients and nutmeats.
Beat until well mixed; pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until inserted toothpick comes out dry.
Top with favorite frosting (my family likes it with peanut butter).

title: broccoli-cauliflower soup
directions: Boil bouillon cubes in 5 cups water until cubes are dissolved. Add noodles; cook until noodles are tender.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Add 5 cups milk (do not add while water is still very hot, milk will curdle).
Add Velveeta cheese and margarine. Cook all slowly, so milk will not curdle until vegetables are tender.

title: tuna that's terrific
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart Hi-Boy or saucepan, prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Preheat 9 3/4 or 10-inch skillet, uncovered, over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Melt butter. Saute onion in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add soup, water, cheese, tuna and pimento.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add spaghetti and heat, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to simmer to keep warm for serving.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to Pam sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook butter, onion and broccoli together, then add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz. Mix with rice.

title: chocolate cornflake squares
directions: Mix and beat until melted, sugar, syrup and peanut butter. Add cornflakes.
Mix and press in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Put in refrigerator and keep until next day or you can roll in balls and dip in chocolate.

title: popeye's special spinach
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw spinach; drain and squeeze dry. Combine spinach, eggs, cottage cheese, butter, flour and Cheddar cheese in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling point and pour over chicken. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Mix ingredients.
Ready to serve when Mozzarella cheese has melted.
Use with cubed bagels or cubed French bread.

title: asparagus and ham
directions: Drain asparagus.
Spread ham with cream cheese.
Roll around asparagus.
Chill and slice in small pieces.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and milk. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Stir in blueberries by hand.
Pile mix high in each cup to make 12 large muffins.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian baked chicken
directions: Pour oil in large pan.
Combine flour and seasoned salt. Remove skin from chicken and dredge pieces in flour mixture. Arrange in baking pan.
Bake 350° for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken and add peppers and carrots to pan and cook 20 minutes longer. (Carrots will be crunchy;
if you want them softer, add them sooner.)
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients except the pineapple, and cook until thickened.
Gently stir in drained pineapple.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake 10 minutes or longer.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: In frying pan, brown chicken pieces in small amount of oil. Remove chicken to ovenproof casserole dish.
To drippings in frying pan, add soup.
Stir well and cook until hot.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: homemade ice cream(low-cal)
directions: Freeze in electric freezer according to freezer directions.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops
directions: Put salt and pepper on pork chops with Tony's, too.
Put on a barbecue grill for 1 or 2 hours.
Add sauce at end of cooking. Take off grill and eat.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients for dressing.
Combine tuna and cucumber.
Just before serving, toss tuna with dressing. Serves 6.
Each serving equals 2 meat exchanges and 1 fat exchange.

title: simple sukiyaki
directions: Heat oil in electric skillet to set at 375° to 400°.
Brown sirloin 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine sugar, flour, soy sauce and water.
Pour over beef; push to one side.
Add bamboo shoots and onions, keeping in separate groups.
Continue cooking while tossing each group 5 to 10 minutes, keeping vegetables separate. Push to side.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts and mushrooms, keeping in groups.
Cook about 2 minutes until heated through. Serve with hot fluffy rice.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Combine first seven ingredients; boil 3 minutes and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in bars when cool.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in 2 cups water (boiling).
Stir in pineapple; chill until partially set.
Fold in cranberry sauce.

title: baked pleated potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; pat dry.
Cut each potato crosswise into 1/8-inch slices, but do not cut all the way through bottom of potato.
Place on a baking sheet.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients.
Brush over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop onion and place in skillet with oil.
Cook until tender. Add ground beef; cook until beef is brown.
Drain excess oil.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Sift flour, 1/2 cup of sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into pan and cover with cherries.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of sugar over top.
Pour hot cherry juice over top and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices.
Mix together soup and wine; spoon over chicken and cheese.
Mix together stuffing mix and butter; place on top of chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir in taco mix, tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat mixture.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted oleo.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/2 cup crumbs.
Soften ice cream and spread over crumbs.
Place in freezer until firm.
Spread fudge topping on top of ice cream.
Sprinkle peanuts over topping.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs over Cool Whip.
Cover with foil and keep in freezer until serving time.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: dill garlic beans
directions: Cook the string beans for about 10 minutes, but leave firm. In each sterile jar, place a sprig of dill, 2 small cloves of garlic and the beans.
Boil together remaining ingredients.
Pour boiling mixture over beans and seal.

title: garlic potato tapa
directions: Mix mustard, dressing, garlic and pepper in a large bowl. Stir in potatoes and onions. Mix lightly. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: steamboats
directions: Shred cheese and mix with enough mayonnaise to hold together as a sauce.
Put meat on a slice of bread.
Top with peeled and sliced avocado.
Cover with cheese and mayonnaise.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pickle delight
directions: Cut liverwurst and cream cheese into strips.
Wrap around pickles, then cut into wheels.
Secure with fancy toothpicks, if needed.

title: strawberry and cream cake
directions: Rinse, cap and slice strawberries.
Pinch cake into small pieces.
Set aside.
Mix berries and glaze.
Set aside.
Combine whipped topping, sour cream, milk and sugar.

title: double rich chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa powder.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.

title: german chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place in 12 x 9-inch cake pan or casserole dish.
Mix remainder of ingredients.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper in bacon drippings.
Add rest of ingredients except shrimp.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cleaned and deveined shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: old fashioned corn light bread
directions: Add the hot water to 1 1/4 cups meal.
Make this into mush. Set off to cool, then add cold water and enough meal to make a thick mush.
This will take 1 1/2 cups meal.
Cover and set in a warm place until the next day.
Let it rise.

title: favorite cocoa frosting
directions: Put in saucepan.
Cook until boiling.
Boil one minute.
Cool and add one teaspoon vanilla.
Spread.

title: chipped ham barbeque
directions: Cook above ingredients until onion is tender.
Add 2 lb. (or more) Chipped or thinly sliced Ham and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: canned sandwich spread
directions: Chop vegetables in food grinder, drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add flour, mustard and water (mixed together like thickening).
Boil 5 minutes longer.
Add Miracle Whip, mix well, pack hot in jars and seal.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add tomatoes (chopped slightly) and tomato paste, water and spices.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread and raisins in baking dish.
Mix and pour remaining ingredients over bread and raisins.
Make sure bread is well soaked.
Bake 40 minutes at 375 degrees.
Use vanilla sauce on top.

title: mrs. kennedy's favorite seafood casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients (except potato chips and paprika) in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, that has been buttered.
Top with potato chips and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: deborah nelson's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and cream together.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Put onto ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Makes a large batch.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix with Bisquick and grated cheese. Add milk.
Mix well and make into balls.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thinly, about 8 cups.
Layer potatoes and sprinkle each layer with dry ingredients.
Dot with remaining butter.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 60 to 70 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Place peanut butter in a medium glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 30 to 40 seconds to soften.
Stir in 1 cup powdered sugar; add the cream until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and stir until well mixed.
Roll the peanut butter cream into 1-inch balls.
Sift remaining powdered sugar over the balls and roll them in sifted powdered sugar.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator.
Yield: 28 Peanut Butter Balls.

title: blue cheese dip for vegetables
directions: Make ahead and let stand.

title: marble squares
directions: Beat until creamy the shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs. Sift and mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut in squares and cool.

title: creamy chicken divan
directions: Prepare Shells and Cheese as directed on the package.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in salad dressing, flour and salt. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Layer Shells and Cheese mixture, broccoli and chicken in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with sauce; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.

title: apple walnut salad
directions: Whisk oil and vinegar.
Add coriander and ground pepper.
Toss together lettuce, walnuts and apples.
Pour on dressing.

title: bubble bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Arrange in Bundt pan.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
