title: potato, carrot, zucchini bake
directions: Combine zucchini and salt in large bowl.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil and saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place half of onions and a coating of oil in 9-inch pie plate.
Squeeze zucchini dry and combine with potatoes, carrots, basil, chives and cheese.
Pat into pie plate and top with remaining onions and garlic.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Pour cream over, lower heat to 350° and cook for 20 to 30 minutes longer or until cooked and browned.

title: fried softshell crawfish
directions: Clean the crawfish by removing the top shell and eyes. Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over the crawfish.
Mix flour and cornmeal in 3 to 1 proportion; season with salt, cayenne pepper, garlic powder and allspice.
Dip crawfish into this mixture and fry in oil for about 3 minutes.

title: e - z cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered with foil, then uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
If desired, cover with crushed corn flakes.

title: macaroni and lots of cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In large saucepan, cook chopped onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper until blended.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the Cheddar and cream cheeses until melted.
Stir macaroni into cheese mixture. Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tomato and green onion.

title: baby wipes
directions: Cut one roll of Bounty paper towels in half.
Place towels upright in airtight container and pour solution over it.
Remove center cardboard.
Cover tightly, and it's ready to use in an hour.
The wipes can be pulled out from center, just like store bought ones.

title: meatballs parmigiana
directions: Arrange noodles in baking dish.
Saute onions in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes and spaghetti sauce and bring to a boil.
In a separate bowl, combine egg, 1/4 cup Parmesan, oregano, bread crumbs, ground chuck, salt and pepper.
Shape into 24 small meatballs.
Add to boiling sauce; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Spoon meatballs over noodles; cover with Mozzarella.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan over top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 polite people, or 4 hungry ones.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix well; spread on cake.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: impossible quiche(makes its own crust)
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle bacon, shredded cheese and onion into pan.
Put remaining ingredients in the blender; blend until smooth.
Pour over cheese in pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand five minutes before serving. This is also great leftover; even cold.

title: mama martin's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add milk, mixing well.
Pour into dry mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter; beat until butter melts.
Pour into baked crust.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve jello flavors separately, using 2 cups boiling water to each of the 6 ounce and 3 ounce packages of jello.
Add 1 cup of marshmallows to the lemon gelatin and set aside.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water to the lime jello.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: chip 'n cherry bread
directions: Beat eggs and stir in sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and combine with nuts, chips and fruit.
Fold in egg mixture.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Place pan of water on bottom rack of oven. Bake loaves on top rack of oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Put this mixture in a large bowl and cover with 1 cup sugar.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream margarine and shortening until smooth.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and continue beating until very creamy.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients, stirring until well blended after each addition.
Add flavoring and beat egg whites until they hold stiff peaks.
Add 1/3 at a time and carefully fold into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake in a 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours (top will be brown and crusty). Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling. Let stand overnight to enhance flavor.

title: banana punch
directions: Put bananas in blender; put sugar in gallon container with 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until sugar dissolves; add about 2 more cups of cold water.
Stir in blended bananas, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Finish filling container with water.
Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, pour in ginger ale.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, soda and sugar.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add this and buttermilk to shortening mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough to 3/4-inch and cut into the size you want.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
You can store leftover dough in refrigerator for the next day.
I like to roll out and cut into biscuits about 1 hour before baking.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix all together in casserole.
Cover.
Stir once.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hearty cabbage soup(a main dish ready in 30 minutes!)
directions: In large heavy saucepan brown kielbasa in oil.
Remove kielbasa.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Stir in salt, thyme and pepper, then cabbage, tomatoes, sausage and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until cabbage is a desired tenderness. Stir in beans.
Cook for a few minutes to heat beans.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Cut oranges in small pieces.
Mix oranges and pineapple well. Add cottage cheese and stir.
Sprinkle dry jello over mixture and stir well, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into dish or mold and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add corn, tomato paste and cooked noodles. Place in casserole dish.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: 3 cheese lasagna rolls
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as label directs.
Mix Ricotta and next 5 ingredients.
Cut noodles in half crosswise and spread 1/4 cup mixture on each half.
Roll in jelly roll fashion.

title: easy blueberry crunch
directions: Layer each ingredient in a 9 x 13 pan in order given.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Prepare pudding with the milk, as directed on package.
Spoon into crusts.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs over pudding to cover.
Push licorice legs into pudding (8 per spider).
Press chocolate candies into place for eyes.

title: grandma croman's boiled spice cake
directions: Put the first 7 items into a pan and bring to a boil.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add the rest of the items.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Does not need frosting.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine salt, soda and flour and sift.
Add alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add flavoring.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven for first hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Mix with next four ingredients. Pour into slightly greased baking dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit trifle - sugar free
directions: Tear cake in small pieces.
Mix drained pineapple and oranges. Make pudding according to directions.
In a 2-quart bowl, layer half the cake pieces, half the fruit and half the pudding. Repeat.
Make the topping and spread over pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serves 8.
Can be doubled and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut up steak in small pieces and brown in shortening.
Set aside.
Place next 7 ingredients in pan and place meat on top. Cover with hot water.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put cheese on top and put back into oven for 15 minutes.

title: curried lima beans
directions: Cook the beans until tender; salt.
Dice the bacon.
Dice the onion and garlic.
Brown onion.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: kathy's breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Spread crescent rolls in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread sausage over rolls.
Add hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-time bread pudding
directions: Put quartered toast into a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish. Sprinkle raisins over toast.
Pour a mixture of the next 6 ingredients over toast.
Let stand 10 minutes, then sprinkle with 4 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: boston market dill potatoes
directions: Scrub and cube potatoes (leave skin on); place in pot with water and boil until tender. Drain and add ingredients. Simmer until butter is melted. Slightly mash potatoes with a fork before serving.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: Bring to
a
boil
the soup, water, salt and onion.
Pour 1/2 in greased
1/2-quart
casserole.
Alternate layers of rice (right from box), peas
and
tuna
until
all is used.
Add remaining soup mixture. Sprinkle with
cheese.
Stir at least once during baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Prepare jello with boiling water.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Stir.
Pour half of strawberry mixture into an 8 x 6-inch pan to gel.
After first layer is firm, spread sour cream on top.
Spread remaining strawberry mixture on top. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole #2
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz and rice while rice is hot.
Saute butter, chopped onions and celery.
Add cooked, drained broccoli and soup. Mix well.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not salt!
Add pepper as desired.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour 6 times with soda added.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add one egg at a time.
Blend well, then add sour cream.
Blend well.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Blend in remaining ingredients together for about two minutes or until batter is creamy.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake turns loose from pan.

title: mom's baked chocolate pudding
directions: Mix and pour over mixture already in baking dish. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Crumble together last 4 ingredients until the consistency of cornmeal.
Place fruit, either canned, fresh or frozen in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumb toppings over fruit.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: *May substitute fruit cocktail.

title: corn muffins
directions: Blend liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Do not overmix (takes about 1 minute).
Bake in greased muffin pan at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 large or 12 small muffins.

title: "south carolina chews"
directions: Drop everything into bowl and stir until mixed.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 12-inch).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top while hot.
Cut and leave in pan to cool.

title: minestrone
directions: Dice ham in small pieces.
Rinse vegetables.
Peel carrots, onion and potatoes.
Slice all vegetables or cut into julienne sticks.
Saute ham and vegetables in oil for a few minutes. Transfer to a large pot.
Add water, bouillon cubes, tomato puree, garlic, pasta and rice.
Cook covered on medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes and thawed peas to soup.
Heat. Season with salt and pepper.

title: light brown bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine next 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; stir until shortening melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°. Add yeast mixture to milk mixture Add 1 cup whole wheat flour and 2 cups bread flour.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining 1 cup whole wheat flour and enough remaining bread flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface, and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt candy bars.
Combine with Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: seashell crab casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
In medium size saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour. Cook 2 minutes (do not brown).
Add milk, salt and cayenne pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens. Add cheese, crab meat and lemon juice. Stir until cheese melts.
Combine sauce with shells.
Pour into 3-quart casserole. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: crab mundoo
directions: Mix cream cheese with Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise. Add crab and green onion and mix well.
Fill mundoo cover (about 1 teaspoon) with crab meat mixture.
Seal edges with beaten egg mixture.
Deep fry.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw Campbell's cream of shrimp soup.
Add cream cheese and shrimp (mashed fine with a fork).
Add lemon juice, garlic powder and paprika.
Blend with a spoon until smooth.
Chill before serving.
Makes enough dip for 12 or more people.
tags: Campbell's frozen cream of shrimp soup

title: honey-peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter and honey.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to peanut butter mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and Kool-Aid with small amount of water. Add pineapple juice, finish filling gallon jug almost full with water. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: orange buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Combine gelatin and pineapple with syrup in a large saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring to prevent sticking.
Cool slightly.
Stir in buttermilk.
Fold in whipped topping and pecans.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: low fat lemon cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Spray bottom of 8 inch spring form pan with cooking spray, sprinkle crumbs in pan. Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Add egg whites, egg, lemon juice, and vanilla. Mix well. Stir in flour, pour into pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set. Chill. Optional, top with fresh fruit. Refrigerate.

title: easy sundae topping
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well mixed.
Ready to use at once or refrigerate.
Serve over ice cream.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with a layer of beef, then cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and dressing; spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices and set aside. Combine butter and bread crumbs in small bowl; sprinkle over tomato slices. Microwave at 70% power for 12 to 14 minutes or bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, crumbled, thoroughly.
Drain.
Add salsa. Place 2 tortillas
on
the
bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 3/4 cup salsa
and	sausage
on
tortillas.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Put 2 more tortillas and continue layering , finishing with cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes and cut into squares.
Can garnish with dollop of sour cream.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine instant soup and water, bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook 10 minutes.
Brown sausage and drain.
Saute pepper and onions in sausage drippings.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Mix
in
order
of ingredients.
Form into small balls, flatten with fork to make a crisscross imprint.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Colored sugar makes it very pretty.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: strawberry rhubarb deep dish cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in strawberries, rhubarb, lemon juice and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until hot, bubbly and slightly thickened.
Pour into 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each in half.
Coat each with melted margarine; roll in sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits, cut side down on hot fruit mixture in circle around edge of casserole, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spinach 'n stuffin
directions: Melt stick margarine.
Stir in bread stuffing crumbs.
Spoon half of mixture in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Mix raw spinach with sour cream and soup mix.
Spoon over bread stuffing, then top with remaining bread stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broken glass
directions: Dissolve each package of jello with hot water.
Pour into separate shallow pans and let stand in refrigerator.
Cut sugar and softened butter into crushed graham crackers with pastry blender or blending fork.
Line oblong glass baking dish (11 x 14-inch) with cracker mixture; use only 2/3 of it.
Soften plain gelatin in cold water; dissolve in hot pineapple juice and set aside to cool.
Whip the cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled pineapple juice to whip cream mixture.
Cut jello into small cubes and blend gently into whip cream mixture.
Pour into crust and spread evenly.
Sprinkle remaining 1/3 cracker mixture on top. Let stand in refrigerator 12 hours or overnight.

title: grilled chile wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan and let boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat; pour into a large bowl and except chicken wings. Let cool. Add chicken wings to the marinade and marinate in fridge at least 2 hours. Grill over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until cooked through. Serve with celery and carrot sticks.

title: pasta deluxe salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain well. Combine pasta, meat, cheese, green pepper and onion; stir well and chill.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, vinegar and sugar; pour over pasta mixture and toss well.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a saucepan, bring the sour cream just to the boiling point. Remove from heat and add oleo.
In a large bowl, beat egg, sugar, salt and soda; then add sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle yeast on this mixture.
Stir well, then add flour.
Knead the dough into a ball.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Roll into strips 6-inches in width and spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold over and cut in strips 1-inch wide.
Press down on greased cookie sheet and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown, cook on brown paper bag and remove immediately.
Freezes well.

title: danish puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cut the butter or margarine into the flour. Sprinkle the water over the mixture and mix with a fork. Round into a ball and divide in half. Place each half in strips, side by side, on an ungreased baking sheet.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion. Cook until wilted; mix with can of corn. Pour over tamales that have been sliced sideways. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: best ever chili
directions: Cook beef, onion or onion powder, peppers and celery until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain beans.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Mix all together well and chill overnight.

title: punch
directions: Mix 1 pint of water to cool aid mix. Mix sugar and water together, pour cool aid into sugar mix. Add rest of ingredients. Serve cold.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Press dough onto 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until browned and puffed.
Cool completely. Beat the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together; spread over cookie.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese.
Chill.

title: black walnut refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and add to cream mixture. Add nuts.
Make 2 rolls; put in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until desired brownness.

title: chicken on rice
directions: Blend mushroom soup and milk.
Set aside 1/2 cup of mixture for later use.
Combine together:
soup mixture, rice and dry soup mix.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour the reserved soup mixture over chicken.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix in bowl the cream cheese, onion, mayonnaise and shrimp. Add about 2 to 3 teaspoons of juice of 1 lemon and other ingredients.
I just add enough paprika to color the dip a pinkish orange.
Refrigerate afterwards.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and peel off most of peeling. Dice and cook potatoes. Set cooked potatoes aside. Combine butter, milk and flour in 5-quart pot. Stir until smooth. Cook on medium, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly. Stir in potatoes, salt, pepper, cheese, bacon and onions. Cook until cheese is melted, but do not boil. Add sour cream.

title: apricot gelatin salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add pineapple to gelatin and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and pineapple juice until smooth. Stir in gelatin mixture, chill until partially set, stirring occasionally.
Stir in apricots and walnuts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into a 13 inch x 9 inch x 2 inch dish.
Sprinkle with walnuts if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: banana-bran bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
At high speed of mixer, beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in banana. Add flour mixture, bran and nuts, beating until smooth.
Turn into prepared pan.
Cook (350° oven) until toothpick inserted into bread comes out clean.
Cool.
Slice.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pack evenly in pot.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar in can of sauce.
Stir and place on top of meat loaf.
Cook on low approximately 6 hours (on high sides will burn).
Start before 8 a.m. and it is ready for supper.
Cut in fourths and remove.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple confetti salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple.
Refrigerate until syrupy.
Add sour cream, nuts and cherries.
Mix well.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set. Unmold.
Garnish with small cream cheese balls rolled in chopped nuts and cherries.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 2 boxes strawberries, bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half of the mixture in a dish and allow to set up.
Mix the sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread over the set up mixture.
Pour the remaining jello on top.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, evaporated milk and a pinch of salt. Finish filling ice cream container with whole milk.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until firm.

title: peanut butter cream pie(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and light cream in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave oven on Full power for 4 to 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir twice during cooking time with wire whisk.
Add egg gradually, stirring with wire whisk.
Cook in oven on Full power for 1 to 2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir twice during cooking.
Add peanut butter, stirring until smooth. Cool.
Turn into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together; let stand for 10 minutes to allow flavors to mingle.
Spread on your favorite meats or poultry, or mix in your favorite recipes.

title: garden chop-chop
directions: Combine tomatoes, green pepper, celery and onion in large bowl. Pour lemon juice over; toss lightly.
Chill at least an hour to blend flavors.
Drain before serving.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake as directed for a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 1 box Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour slowly on cooled cake.
Beat pudding, Jell-O, vanilla and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on cake and refrigerate.

title: mother's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; set aside.
Crumble biscuits and add cheese, margarine and cold water in a saucepan.
Cook until cheese melts.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Salt and pepper.
Mix a little of the hot cheese mixture with the egg mixture and beat. Then pour eggs into cheese mixture and cook until thick.
Add macaroni and cook a little longer.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Combine eggs, mushrooms, carrots, onions and spinach.
Mix well.
To the egg mixture, add garlic powder, Ricotta or cottage cheese and salt (to taste).
In the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spoon a thin layer of spaghetti sauce.
Layer with lasagna noodles, Mozzarella, egg-cheese-vegetable mixture, spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with lasagna noodles, sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake, uncovered, 25 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mother's irish freckle bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in potato water.
Add potatoes, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth and let rise until bubbly (about 1/2 hour).
Stir down; add remaining sugar, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in beaten eggs, then oleo. Add raisins.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto floured pastry cloth and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place into greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: oven-baked round steak
directions: Place steak on sheet of aluminum foil.
Top with soup mix and mushrooms.
Lightly close foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and bananas.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to batter and blend well.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in greased large loaf pan one hour at 325°.

title: skillet herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.

title: oatmeal jumble bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except preserves.
Mix well. Reserve 1 cup mixture.

Press remaining onto bottom of prepared pan. Spread preserves evenly over base to within 1/2-inch of edge of pan. Sprinkle with reserved mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely. Cut into bars.
Makes a 13 x 9-inch pan of bars.

title: carrie's favorite cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and other ingredients.
Beat well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in ground pecans.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out raised bread until thin.
Separate eggs; spread yolks over top of dough.
Sprinkle oregano and garlic salt on top.
Lay slices of Provolone and Mozzarella cheese over mixture.
Top with pepperoni slices and hamburger combination (onions, salt, green pepper and meat fried up).
Roll like a jelly roll.
Brush with egg whites.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix cornmeal and water and stir until thick.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir and pour over meat mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popped corn, M&M's, peanuts and nuts in a large bowl. Melt butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Pour over corn mixture. Butter hands well and mix.
Place in a well buttered tube pan. Invert on a plate when ready to serve.

title: caramel sticks
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into a greased pan (1 1/2 x 6 1/2 x 10 1/2-inches).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Cut and roll in powdered sugar. Makes 24 sticks.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In large glass bowl, layer all ingredients (except mayo) in order.
Top layers with mayo.
Cover with Saran.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve hot, mixed.
Will hold for several days.

title: spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream margarine and sugar; mix in egg. Add molasses and water. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves. Mix dry mixture to sugar mixture. Add in orange rind and refrigerate a few hours to allow ingredients to settle. Roll into 1-inch balls and then roll into sugar. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice. Add juice to a 3-quart heavy-duty pot. Add sugar and cornstarch and mix well. Add pineapple and chopped apples. Simmer until juice is a thin syrupy consistency. May cool in pan over ice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or any pretty glass bowl and cover with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: summer tuna or salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or as sandwich filling.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3 inches).
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened; beat vigorously 1 minute.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen; remove from pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: broken bowl casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package, then put aside. Microwave meatballs until heated through.

title: special black-eyed peas
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Saute chopped vegetables in the bacon fat. Add peas and tomatoes.
Add crumbled bacon.
Simmer 40 minutes. Serves 8.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together and
beat
with
electric mixer 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternately with cream of coconut.
Mix until blended after each addition. Stir in lemon rind and vanilla.
Pour batter into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. A very good pound cake.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine salmon, bread crumbs, chopped onion, butter, salt and pepper; mix well.
Combine milk and egg; add to salmon mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf in a greased shallow baking pan or in a greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place about 8 pork chops on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Bring to a boil the water and sugar; cool.
Add beaten egg, bananas, pineapple, orange juice, cherries and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into plastic container; cover and place in freezer.
Stir frequently while in process of freezing so fruit does not settle in bottom.
Slightly defrost before serving.

title: sweetheart cheese tarts
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer inside cupcake line in pan, flat side down.
Cream together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Spoon creamed mixture into 24 cups.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. While this is baking, prepare the sour cream, sugar and vanilla topping.
Spoon on top of tarts and bake another 10 minutes.
When cool, top with pie cherries or blueberries.

title: quick chicken with veggies
directions: Clean chicken and season with salt, pepper and garlic powder (just a little).
Make a bed with heavy duty aluminum foil.
Place chicken and cut up veggies in foil; fold securely.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes, checking periodically.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash and onion well. Beat with mixer.
Add all additional ingredients and beat again.
Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, salt, sugar, nutmeg and soda; then add eggs.
Next add pumpkin, water and oil.
Mix well, then add nuts, raisins and dates.
Grease and flour well four 1-pound coffee cans. Fill cans 1/2 full and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake one hour at 325°.
You can take from the cans while hot.
Serve with whipped cream.
(Olive-cream cheese spread can be used with bread.)

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies according to directions on box; crumble up when cool.
Make chocolate pudding according to directions.
Crumble candy bars into very small pieces.
Layer into large crystal bowl as follows:
1/2 brownie crumbles, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 candy bars. Repeat layers, then put the chocolate Cool Whip on top.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix all together and pour into serving bowl.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cut chicken into bite sized pieces.
Combine with Ro-tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup, water and seasoning.
Simmer over low heat. Cut tortillas into 1/4-inch strips and fry until crisp.
Drain excess fat.
Spoon soup into bowl.
Garnish with avocados, cheese and fried tortilla strips.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix in pan, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water in gradually, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Stir until thick. Remove from heat.

title: shoepeg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: creole chicken and grits
directions: Combine 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup oil in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, 20 to 30 minutes or until roux is caramel-colored.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute 4 minutes.
Add chicken broth, tomato sauce and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer over low heat 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over and last 3 ingredients as toppings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spicy chicken chili
directions: In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, warm oil.
Add chicken, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: onion relish
directions: Saute onions, celery and red pepper in butter in a small Dutch oven for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Add vinegar and the remaining ingredients to the mixture.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Store in refrigerator. Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Yields 1 quart.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs.
Add sweet potatoes.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
(Note:
Can line pans with wax paper.) Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool and ice with Fluffy Egg White Icing.

title: walnut-romaine salad
directions: In screw-top jar, put oil, honey, vinegar, wine, ginger and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover and shake well.
Chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: hayride cookies
directions: Melt together over low heat 1 1/2 sticks margarine, vanilla, 2 tablespoons sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Remove from heat; stir like custard.
Add graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 6 tablespoons margarine, milk, pudding and 3 cups powdered sugar.
Spread on crust layer.
Chill.
Melt chocolate chips with 1 1/2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Spread as icing on top of pudding layer.
Refrigerate until almost firm. Cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and add 1 cup chicken broth or water.
Pour in casserole dish and top with a mixture of crushed Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beans ranchero style soup
directions: Cook beans until done.
Add all ingredients.
Let simmer 1/2 hour, then add salt and pepper to taste.
Add own hot sauce, if desired.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Cream cheese and dry jello together.
Add 1 cup hot water. Stir until mixed.
Add 7-Up and marshmallows.
Add pecans.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: hot macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Blend tomatoes; add to macaroni and simmer for a few minutes.
If ground beef is used, it may need to simmer about 10 minutes longer.

title: winter potage
directions: Dice tomatoes into saucepan; add potatoes, onion, salt and a few grains pepper.
Add boiling water; cook until tender.
Mix sour cream and flour together in double boiler; cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir sour cream mixture gradually into tomato-potato mixture.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper.
Reheat but do not boil.

title: kringler
directions: Use enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Take a small piece of dough and roll into long round strips, forming figure eights. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: quick yeast spoon rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water; stir.
Combine butter, sugar and beaten egg, then add flour.
Mix well.
Spoon into muffin pans. Bake at 400° until brown.
Keep remainder in a sealed bowl.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Then poke holes through cake with fork.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: chocolate peanut butter frosting
directions: Combine and beat until creamy the peanut butter, chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Add and beat, until smooth, the confectioners sugar alternately with milk.
Fills and frosts 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix together the sugar, cornstarch and cloves in saucepan, then add vinegar, beet juice and butter.
Cook, stirring until thick and clear.
Add sliced beets and let heat until beets are heated through.

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Cook sugar, beaten egg, flour and pineapple juice until thick. Cool this mixture and add to the pineapple, cheese and marshmallows.
Stir until all ingredients are coated.

title: dream-cicle cake
directions: Bake according to directions in round cake pan.
Cool and slice in half.
Put Filling between layers.

title: starlight cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in long baking dish.
In a bowl mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour in butter pan.
Do not stir.
Spoon peaches on dough and bake at 375° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread and let rise as directed.
Push dough down.
Roll out in rectangle on cookie sheet.
Down the center, place 1/2 the cheese mixture, then beef and sausage.
Next put pepperoni and Canadian bacon, then layer bell pepper and onion; top with remaining cheese.
Roll up edges of dough and pinch edges together. Place seam side down.
Brush with butter and sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: *Thaw bread overnight in refrigerator; do not let rise.

title: spinach-orange salad
directions: Combine spinach and next 4 ingredients in a bowl; toss gently. Serve with Yogurt Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: opal critchfield's pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast liberally with seasoned salt on both sides. Rub pepper over roast and place in roasting pan.
Pour 1 cup of the water in pan and cook for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add the vegetables around the roast and cook for 1 hour more.
Remove roast to serving platter.

title: seafood risotto
directions: In large, heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium heat.
Add shrimp and scallops.
Saute until shrimp begins to color.
Add garlic; saute 2 minutes more.
Add tomatoes; toss to combine.
Set aside.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in the bottom of a greased oblong pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions and pour into pan over nuts and coconut.
Melt and brown butter.
Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar until smooth (will be thick like icing).
Pour mixture over top of cake mix.
(May drop by spoonfuls because of difficulty to cover cake mix.)
Extremely delicious! Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: two minute fudge
directions: *Can substitute coconut, peanut butter or raisins.

title: cavatini(casserole)
directions: *May substitute 1/2 cup rotini, 1/2 cup shells and 1/2 cup tube-type
pasta (mostaccioli).

title: baked banana squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
To form crust combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, mixing well.
Press into the bottom 8 inch square pan and pan should be greased.
Bake 5 minutes or until brown.
Next create the banana topping by melting the butter in a medium saucepan.
Add lemon rind and juice and banana cuts and stir until bananas are coated with butter.
Arrange banana slices on crust.
Sprinkle brown sugar over bananas.
Bake 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Cut into 2 inch squares.
Yields 16 squares.

title: cherry-apricot freezer jam
directions: Wash apricot halves and cherries; drain thoroughly in a colander.
Finely chop the fruit.
(You should have a total of about 2 1/2 cups chopped fruit.)
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the chopped fruit, sugar, lemon juice and almond extract. Cover loosely; let the mixture stand for 10 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake or steam 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Boil chicken breasts in large pan until done, 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pot. Cut or separate into bite size pieces. Put chicken and can of soup into a large pan.
Add 1 can water, minced onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until hot. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, place biscuits on top.
Place in oven.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are done at 350°.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: To make oat flour, process 2 1/2 cups uncooked oats in covered blender 30 seconds.
Scrape down and repeat.
Makes approximately 1 3/4 cups oat flour.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Alternately add milk and flour mixture.
Spread in 10 or 12-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate cake flour and liquids until well blended.
Last fold in chopped cherries.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until mixed good (30 minutes).
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry or peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and stir until blended. Pour batter over butter in baking dish.
Do not stir.
Pour in fruit; sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: diabetic fudge
directions: Melt chocolate
in
top
of
double
boiler over boiling water.
Add evaporated
milk and mix.
Cook for 2 or 3 minutes. Add vanilla and
sweetener.
Spread on small foil pan or plate. Chill.
Cut into 8 pieces.

title: creamy nut icing
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add flour and salt.
Stir in milk slowly.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in brown sugar.
Remove from heat, stir in powdered sugar.
Let cool and blend in vanilla and chopped nuts.
This is very good on angel food cake.

title: cherry icebox cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars, adding eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla. Sift flour and soda, using 1 cup of the mixture to coat the fruit and nuts.
Add remaining flour to the sugar mixture and mix well. Chill dough so it will handle easily.
Then divide into 4 equal portions and shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and foil. Freeze until ready to bake.
Cut into thin slices and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
If they are sliced too thick, they will not be crisp, but like a cake.

title: green beans with wheat biscuits
directions: Place ingredients in baking dish.
Combine 3 rounded shredded wheat biscuits, crumbled, and 3 tablespoons of melted butter or margarine; sprinkle over green bean base.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green beans
directions: Mix all together and heat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into buttered baking dish, keeping dry crumbs close to the top, so that no zucchini is exposed.
Save a little of the dressing mix to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together. Store in dry container. Stir in 1 heaping teaspoonful per cup hot water or more to taste.

title: e-z cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar to taste and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Drain pineapple and add other ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in M&M candies and drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: south american beans and rice
directions: Spray a large, heavy skillet with Pam.
Saute garlic and onion until transparent.
Add celery and cook for 1 minute.
Add rice and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add beans, red pepper and meat, if using.
Cover tightly and simmer until all liquid is absorbed.
Right before serving, stir in 1 cup of chopped, fresh tomatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Mix soups, enchilada sauce, green chilies and milk; bring to a boil.
Crunch chips and place in a greased casserole dish.
Pour meat over chips, then pour soup mixture over the top of all the meat.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together well.
Cook in slow oven (300°).

title: potato supreme
directions: Cook potatoes (peeling on) until just tender.
Peel and grate potatoes coarsely.
Add butter, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, onions and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix well.
Bake in buttered casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place remaining cheese on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: jalapeno cocktail pie
directions: Sprinkle peppers in well-greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over and do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cool at least 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Take 1 cup of faith and spread generously through each lovely day God has given you.
Add one package of hope for every good deed.
Thank God for giving you grace that you need.
Take 2 cups of charity; sift all around to your friends, neighbors, anyone you've found.
Bake for a lifetime and ice it with love.
You have the recipe for Heaven above.

title: easy made pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in a 1/2 gallon jar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Finish filling jar with cold water and seal jar tight.
Let stand 2 weeks.
They can stand for a year. When ready to use, drain and wash cucumbers and slice or chunk. Cover with 3 or 4 cups sugar.
Let stand until sugar makes a syrup.
Put in jar and keep in icebox.
Very good.

title: jambalaya sauce
directions: Cook ham in butter until lightly browned.
Add onions, garlic and peppers.
Cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer to desired thickness.
Ladle into 6 clean hot pint Mason jars, leaving 1 inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; adjust lids. Process in pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure for 75 minutes.

title: mexican chicken and bean casserole
directions: Pour enough enchilada sauce into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish to coat the bottom.
Slice tortillas into wide strips.
Place half of the strips to cover bottom of dish.
Add beans to cover tortillas.
Add chicken over beans.
Pour 1/2 of the enchilada sauce over the chicken.
Cover chicken with remaining tortilla strips.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over the strips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, salsa, cilantro and onions.

title: amy's oriental
directions: Cook beaten egg in the butter in a 10-inch skillet until set. Add onion and rice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add carrots, broccoli and chicken.
Stir until combined.
Add water and soy sauce.
Stir until rice is browned.
Serve.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together until light and fluffy. Add egg and oil and mix well. Add oats, corn flakes, coconut, pecans and vanilla and mix well. Sift flour, soda and salt and add to other mixture. Mix well. Mix all together well and shape into balls the size of a walnut. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Dip a fork into melted butter and then into sugar to flatten balls. This is important because it makes the top of cookies crispy. Bake 12 minutes at 325°. Leave on cookie sheet to cool slightly before removing. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: our favorite chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a mixing bowl; add liquid ingredients and mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Also great for cupcakes.

title: cranberry-jalapeo salsa
directions: Pulse fresh cranberries in a food processor or blender until minced. Transfer minced cranberries to a small bowl. Pulse orange and next 4 ingredients in food processor 3 to 5 times or until mixture is finely chopped. Stir into cranberries; cover and chill if desired. Garnish if desired.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool and split layers crosswise.
Mix sour cream, powdered sugar and coconut.
Mix well (reserve 1 1/2 cups).
Spread in between layers and stack.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip to reserved portion and mix well.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Put in refrigerator for 48 hours, covered.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and cook until crisp.
Add sliced onion and cook until tender.
Drain bacon grease.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to simmer and cook about 10 minutes.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain fat.
In a saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour and salt.
Add milk, all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in cooked sausage, sliced eggs and drained corn.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: taco beef casserole
directions: Layer broken chips in bottom of 2-quart oblong casserole. Brown meat with minced onions.
Drain off grease.
Mix in tomatoes and soup.
Put in casserole over chips.
Top with grated cheese and more broken taco chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: work person's roast
directions: Place roast in center of large sheet of aluminum foil.
Cut slits in roast and push cuts of garlic in cuts.
Pour can of soup over roast.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over soup.
Sprinkle on the dry onion soup mix.
Pull foil up and seal tightly across top and ends.
Leave space above and around roast for expansion.
Place in cake pan and roast in 200° oven for 10 hours.
This recipe can be done in slow cooker.

title: little white cookies
directions: Mix together oleo and sugar; add vanilla and blend well.
Add flour and then pecans until well mixed.
Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 275° to 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Roll in powdered sugar again when cool.

title: sausage stew
directions: In large pot put thin sliced sausage, sliced potatoes and onions.
Cover with at least 1 inch water and paprika.
Salt to taste.
While this is cooking, make dumplings.

title: potatoes chantilly
directions: Put mashed potatoes (slightly dry) in buttered baking dish. Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and top is lightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: In
bowl,
put
lettuce as first layer, followed by the layer of
onion,
bell
pepper, peas and cheese.
Do not stir. Seal with
mayonnaise.
Sprinkle
sugar on top, then sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: pennsylvania dutch light ginger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vinegar. Blend in remaining ingredients.(If dough is too dry to handle easily, work in milk or cream, 1 tsp. at a time.)
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6-8 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.
If desired, decorate with icing.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain well, then add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with next 4 ingredients.
Place half the noodles in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread half the cottage cheese mixture over; add half meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Beat yolks and brown sugar and oil until smooth.
Add pumpkin and blend.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: white cake icing
directions: Mix water, 1 1/2 c. sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Boil until mixture spins a thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar and cooked syrup while beating.
Add 4 tablespoons 4x sugar.
Add vanilla and beat until stiff.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all together except pie shells.
Put in pie shell and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Place raisins in a bowl along with the butter and soda.
Pour boiling water over all; stir.
Let set overnight.
Add eggs, cinnamon, salt, sugar, vanilla and flour.
(Add nuts.)
Fill three greased and floured coffee cans (1 pound size) half full.
Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Cool and slice.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan.
Add green peppers, onion, salt and pepper.
Fry until tender.
Add tomato sauce and water. Stir well.
Cook rice in salt water.
Add to meat and sauce mixture.
Place in well-greased casserole dish.
Top with grated sharp or medium sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: aromatic dry spice blend
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well. Transfer to a jar.
Close tightly.
Keeps indefinitely in a cool, dry place.

title: paprika potato
directions: Saute onion in fat.
Add paprika and potatoes, sliced 1/8-inch thick.
Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until tender. Simmer slowly; cover.
Add salt and pepper.
To sour cream, blend in flour.
Add to potatoes.
Bring to boil and it's done!

title: aplets
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup applesauce.
Bring to a boil rest of applesauce, sugar and salt.
Add to gelatin mixture and boil 15 minutes.
Remove from stove and add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan and let set for 2 days in refrigerator. Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken
directions: Mommy puts white stuff on it, then she bakes it in the oven and it looks like chicken with rice and vegetables.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Put ground meat in pan with onion and brown.
Boil broccoli. When broccoli is tender, pour into a large bowl with ground meat. Add mushrooms and cream cheese.
Pour into pie shells, uncooked. Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco fiesta salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions. Add taco seasoning. Mix beans, lettuce, chopped tomatoes, and cheese. Mix real good, then add Fritos, crushed, and beans. Mix well. Then add the hamburger and Ranch dressing. Mix well. Then some in plate and add some salsa, cheese dip and sour cream. It is awesome.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Wash zucchini.
Do not peel.
Grate with coarse grater.
Place grated zucchini in sieve and press out moisture.
Combine eggs, flour, cheese, salt, chives, garlic and oregano.
Mix with drained shredded zucchini.
Heat shortening in skillet.
Shortening should be about 1/4-inch deep.
Pour large tablespoonful of batter onto griddle for each pancake.
Fry first side until light brown, 1 or 2 minutes.
Turn and fry on other side.
Serve with sour cream or tomato sauce and grated Parmesan.
Yields about 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix together all but Oreos.
Place 1/2 of crushed Oreos evenly in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Pour chocolate mix evenly over cookies.
Top with remaining Oreos.
Chill 1hour.

title: baked custard
directions: Add sugar to eggs and add butter to milk.
Mix all together including vanilla.
Pour into a large bowl.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Pour bowl in pan of hot water to bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Brush 9 x 13-inch baking pan with 2 tablespoons soft butter. Cover bottom with brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple and cherries on sugar mixture.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps well for several days.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease muffin pans well.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter with sugar with electric mixer until soft and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until well blended.
With fork, mash 1/2 cup of blueberries and stir into mixture.
Add rest of whole blueberries, mixing in gently.
Fill pans about 3/4 full. Sprinkle each with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool in pans for 1/2 hour before removing.
Yields 18 muffins in 2 1/2-inch pans or 12 muffins in 3-inch pans.

title: tricia's blueberry salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate until set.

title: italian chicken
directions: Marinate breasts in dressing overnight.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and wrap bacon around each.
Cover bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish with chipped beef. Arrange chicken on top.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Spread pineapple in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Add pie filling and sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling.
Top with pecans.
Combine melted margarine and pineapple juice.
Drizzle over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cut in squares and top with whipped cream.

title: a good chocolate cake
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.

title: hunan pork stir-fry
directions: Cut pork across the grain into thin slices, then into strips. Combine 2 tablespoons each cornstarch and lite soy sauce with 1/2 of the garlic in small bowl; stir in pork.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Sift dry ingredients together into bowl. Pour oil and milk into measuring cup, without stirring.
Then pour all at once into flour, and stir until mixture cleans sides of bowl.
Put into baking dish and bake.

title: rolls
directions: Use
electric
mixer.
Heat
milk, then add sugar, salt and shortening,
stirring
until
all
is dissolved;
cool to lukewarm.
Put
yeast in bowl with warm water to dissolve; add milk
mixture
to
yeast
mixture.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth, then add rest of flour and knead well.
Put in greased
bowl
and
grease the top of the dough.
Let rise about 1
hour,
then
knead
well.
Roll
out and put in your baking sheets; let rise again at least another hour or longer. Bake at 400°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add taco seasoning and mix according to package directions.
Add 1/2 cup picante sauce.
Let all liquid cook out.
Add onto pizza crust the meat and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° until done.
Cut into pieces as desired. Add lettuce, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Put back in oven long enough to slightly melt cheese.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift
flour,
soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.	Stir in flavorings; beat
in flour
mixture alternately with sour cream.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Finely chop artichoke hearts; add to softened cream cheese. Blend; add 1 cup Parmesan and mayonnaise.
Mix well with dash of garlic powder.
Pour in pie plate and sprinkle with bread crumbs and dill weed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: pumpkin blossoms
directions: Pick pumpkin flowers early in the morning, before they start to close.
Pick out center and wash thoroughly.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Dip flowers in egg mixture and then coat with cracker crumbs.
Fry until golden brown.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and add salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out juice and add carrot and green pepper.
While cabbage is standing or you may make this ahead:
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Cool thoroughly and pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Place in containers and freeze.
This may be refrozen and slaw still remains crisp.

title: turkey-pineapple stir-fry
directions: Cut turkey into narrow strips.
Combine 2 tablespoons each of cornstarch and soy sauce with sherry and garlic.
Stir in turkey. Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserve syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to measure 1 cup.
Combine with remaining cornstarch and soy sauce.
Set aside. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat. Add turkey and stir-fry 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove.
Heat remaining oil in same wok.
Add onions, peppers and ginger. Stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Stir in turkey, tomatoes, pineapple and soy sauce mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce boils and thickens.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: steaked spaghetti
directions: Mix all together and bake 45 minutes at 375° in oven.

title: butter sponge cake
directions: Put melted butter in last.
Use 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix together the ingredients and spread on top and bottom of chicken breasts.
Marinate overnight.
Take out chicken and roll in bread crumbs.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over the chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drizzle more butter over the chicken and bake 15 minutes longer.
This is good with brown rice.

title: apple slices
directions: Put egg and milk in cup; mix.
Add to crust and mix.
Roll out half of dough and put on large cookie sheet with sides.
Put 2 handfuls of cornflake crumbs over dough.

title: slow roasted chicken
directions: Prepare grill with coals surrounding a drip pan for indirect heat.
Brush chicken with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put on grill over drip pan.
Roast until chicken is cooked through, about 1 hour 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low calorie tuna-broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a large saucepan. Stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring until hot and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Stir in egg yolks, tuna, broccoli, cheese, onions and seasonings.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry in medium bowl with electric mixer at high speed.
Fold tuna mixture into egg whites.
Spoon into 6-cup casserole or souffle dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown and firm to touch.
Yields 4 servings, 250 calories per serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in fresh bell peppers.
Cook in heavy pot or Dutch oven.
Cover peppers with tomato paste or sauce.
Turn heat high until cooking, then turn heat down and let cook about 45 minutes or until done.
Cook on top of stove.

title: bean salad
directions: Wash and drain butter beans, kidney beans and waxed beans. Mix all beans together.
Slice onion and green pepper; add to mixture.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer chicken in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cooked broccoli; cut in pieces.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, Durbec's, lemon juice, curry and pepper; cover chicken and broccoli.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with cucumber and almond.
Cook 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour to creamed mixture, alternating with milk and orange juice, beginning and ending with flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in orange rind and flavorings.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake in three 8-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cake cool.
Frost with next 3 ingredients.
The longer it sets the better it tastes.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Cut up chicken cutlets and coat with flour.
Melt butter in a frying pan and saute chicken pieces for 10 minutes.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.
If you find gravy too thick, add water.
If it's too watery, add flour.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Spread each bread slice with butter; place bread, buttered side down, in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with cheeses; sprinkle with chiles.
Combine eggs and remaining ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Uncover and bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour, or until lightly browned.
Let casserole stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread & butter pickles
directions: Drain pickles of all juice, and then discard liquid.
Slice the pickles.
Pour sugar over pickles and add hot sauce.
Add garlic. Stir and put into container with tight fitting lid.
Stir once a day for seven days.
Put pickles into jars.

title: two bean lasagna
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over high heat, cook zucchini, peppers and onion until tender and lightly
browned (10 minutes).
Spoon 1/2 mix into a bowl and reserve.
Into vegetables in skillet, stir tomatoes in puree, picante sauce, bouillon, cumin and oregano. Heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low, simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, until slightly thickened.

title: creamed eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs.
Peel.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add flour and seasoning.
Stir until well blended.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth.
Chop eggs and add to sauce.
Serve on toast.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Then mix until smooth the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 3 eggs. Pour over cake mix. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with damp paper towel.
Twist off stems.
Chop stems very fine and place in small mixing bowl with onion and butter.
Saute, uncovered, 4 to 5 minutes.
Combine mixture with bread crumbs, hot pepper sauce and sherry; mix well.
Fill caps with stuffing and place in 8-inch baking dish.
Brown in boiler.

title: polenta al pomodoro
directions: Cook polenta according to package directions, salting according to taste.
Pour polenta in buttered casserole dish. Spoon tomato sauce on top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan.
Sprinkle with olive oil or dot with margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° until crusty and golden brown.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Blend all ingredients in a bowl.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using water and eggs.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish that has been greased and floured or sprayed good with Pam.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Sprinkle sugar, cocoa and nuts evenly over cake batter.
Pour hot water over top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Delicious with Cool Whip, ice cream or plain.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: Butter pan, layer onions, herbs and chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and lemon.
Roast 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven (do not overcook).

title: broccoli bread
directions: Bake in greased pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes on cookie sheet. Immediately remove from oven and spread 1 (7 ounce) jar or 2 cups Marshmallow Creme on cake.

title: healthy fruit compote
directions: Wash and core apples.
Do not peel.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
Add undrained pineapple chunks.
Peel and cut oranges and bananas into bite sized chunks.
Add fresh or frozen strawberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Great for a large crowd.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: avocado-bean dip
directions: Mix avocado with 1 teaspoon lemon juice and garlic salt to taste.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer ingredients as follows:
spread bean dip, then put avocado mix over dip.
Next, put mayo mix and next cheese, green onions and olives.
Layer again if enough.

title: hungarian meat goulash
directions: Cube meat and set aside.
Chop onion fine.
Put in large Dutch oven with 2 tablespoons margarine.
When onion is browned, add meat, salt, pepper and paprika.
Let it all brown until juice comes from it.
Then add 3 to 4 cups of water, plus bouillon cubes.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Stir now and then.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Boil until soft ball stage (236°).
Cool.
Add peanut butter.
Beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: white cake
directions: Mix the usual way and bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix by box directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake as soon as it is removed from oven. Cool completely.
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
Add coconut to Cool Whip and spread on cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: turkey macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Mix mayonnaise, cream, celery, salt and pepper together and add macaroni, turkey, grapes and walnuts.
Chill.

title: barbecue(slow cooker)
directions: Brown beef or roast.
Cook all in slow cooker on high 8 hours or on low for 12 to 16 hours.
Use wire whisk until meat shreds. Serve on buns or over potatoes.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding ginger ale last.
Pour over sherbet and serve.

title: berried delight
directions: Hull and halve the strawberries.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat softened cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Arrange strawberries in an even layer.
Using 3 1/2 cups cold milk.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Pour over berries.
Chill several hours or overnight. Before serving, put remaining topping on top.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones.
Combine in a large bowl the cheese, dressing and seasonings.
Add salmon to mixture.
A delicious spread for pumpernickel bread, crackers or as a dip.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press biscuits into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
(Note: Refrigerator pizza crust can also be used to make crust.) Bake until slightly golden.
Allow to cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing.
Spread on cooled crust.
Cover with vegetables and top with cheese.
Cut into wedges and serve!

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss gently.
Chill before serving.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour and bring to full boil.
Add dry jello and pie filling and mix.
Cool.
Add nuts and sliced bananas and pour into two 9-inch baked pie shells (or 3 small pie shells).
Top with a whipped topping.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add sour milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix in.
Add nuts, cherries and dates. Stir well.
Chill one hour.
Bake by teaspoonfuls in 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Pour water over Jell-O.
Let stand to cool.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Add juice to cheese and beat until creamy.
Add cheese mixture, pineapple, pecans and 7-Up to Jell-O.
Chill to set.
Serve as squares on lettuce leaves.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine and mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Press into ungreased cookie sheet with sides, spreading evenly in pan.
Melt together chocolate bits and butter.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut in squares.

title: friendship tea
directions: In a large bowl, combine instant tea, lemonade powder, orange drink mix, cinnamon and cloves. Mix well and store in an airtight container.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and shred potatoes, place in a bowl of cold water.
Line a colander with paper towels.
Drain potatoes in colander, and squeeze out as much moisture as possible.
Place potatoes in mixing bowl, add eggs, onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Heat about 1/3 cup oil in a skillet until hot.
Drop potato mixture 1/4 cup at a time into hot oil, about 3 inches apart.
Flatten with pancake turner to make a 4-inch pancake.
Cook pancakes until golden brown, turn and cook other side, about 4 minutes total. Remove to a cookie sheet lined with paper towels to drain.
Repeat until all pancakes are cooked.
Serve immediately or place in a warm oven until ready to serve.
Serve with sugar, maple syrup or applesauce.
Makes about 16 pancakes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate about 4 hours before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: macaroni 'n cheese(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain and put in casserole dish. Add butter, eggs, cheese and milk. Mix thoroughly.
Cook in a 325° oven until brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lime jello twist
directions: Prepare Jell-O as box directs.
When Jell-O is starting to set, mix in pears and pineapple.
Let Jell-O set for approximately 3 to 4 hours.

title: pizza
directions: Put wax paper down on flat surface. Put 1 tsp. of flour on wax paper. Put biscuits in flour. Take out of flour and roll out with a rolling pin. Put sauce on dough. Add cheese and pepperoni. Cook in oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese with onions.
Smear ham slice with mixture, then roll up.
Place on plate.
Put in freezer until slightly frozen.
Slice 1/2-inch slices.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes on cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients together, except cornflakes and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: cranberry cake squares(low-fat and cholesterol)
directions: *Low-fat and cholesterol version.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix in bowl with hands.
Grease loaf pan.
Place bacon slices on top.
Pour boiling water to make 1/2 inch in bottom of pan. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: stack cake
directions: Put dried apples in heavy pan.
Cover with water and cook with lid on for 15 minutes, adding a little water if needed to keep apples from sticking.
Remove from heat.
Mash with fork and stir in brown sugar, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and cloves.
Return to heat and simmer, stirring, until fruit is soft, thick and spicy. Turn off heat and let pot sit, covered, until ready to use.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Cook onion and potato in broth, then add chicken and other ingredients.
Simmer a few minutes and you are ready to eat.

title: peach bavarian
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add 2/3 cup of peach syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend almond extract into whipped topping.
Gently blend into gelatin; add peaches.
Pour into large casserole dish (9 x 13 inches).
Chill until firm.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Break up ground beef and saute in skillet over medium heat in oil until browned.
Add onion and celery; saute for 5 minutes. Stir in soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and salt.
Remove from heat.
Place half the potatoes in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spoon half the meat mixture over potatoes.
Cover with remaining potatoes, salt and the rest of the meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: tyler pudding pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add eggs, melted butter, milk and vanilla. Beat well.
Put in pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm. Makes 2 pies.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in greased casserole.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: For sauce, in a medium mixing bowl, stir together the soup, milk, marjoram and pepper.
Set aside.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half of each of the ham, onion, potatoes and sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until the potatoes are nearly tender.

title: party chicken wings
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick over medium heat. Add wing pieces and cook until golden brown on all sides, about 6 to 10 minutes. Drain excess liquid.
