Mix remaining ingredients and add to skillet, stirring to coat chicken well. Cook on medium heat until chicken is well coated and sauce thickens, about 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 36 pieces.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the apples.
Mix until crumbly.
Place 1/2 mixture in greased dish.
Place apples on top. Add remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt the butter or margarine; cream this with the sugar in a large bowl, then add the egg which has been beaten.
Add the yeast (which has been dissolved in the warm water) to the creamed mixture.
Then add the flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in an airtight bowl and keep in the refrigerator.
Should be placed in refrigerator overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Stir mixture in large mixing bowl.
Stir in flour until consistency of cake batter.
Let rise to double in bulk, 3 hours. Work down; stir in more flour until you can knead well.
Place in refrigerator.
Pinch off amount as needed.
Place on floured surface.
Roll and cut out.
Place in baking pan; let rise 30 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate pinch me cake
directions: Flatten out each biscuit and put one Kiss (pointed side up) on each biscuit.
Pinch sides together to make a ball.
Dip in butter and roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In
x
10-inch
glass
pan, place 8 chicken breasts. Cover each
with	1 thin slice tomato, few fresh sliced mushrooms
and one
slice of cheese.
Mix soup and wine together; pour
over chicken.
Cover
with crushed croutons and dribble melted
butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: cool rise bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl; blend well.
Add hot water.
Add margarine or oil.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup of flour.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute or until thick and elastic.
Gradually stir in enough of the remaining flour with a wooden spoon to make a soft dough which leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn dough onto a floured board and knead for 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover with Saran Wrap, then a towel.
Let rest for 20 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together with the mixer.
Serve with your favorite fruits.

title: fruit betty
directions: Put fruit in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with juice and cinnamon.
In a food processor, fitted with the metal blade, place flour, sugar and oleo.
Pulsing on and off, process until consistency of coarse meal.
Sprinkle over berries.
(Dish can be covered and refrigerated up to 10 hours at this point; add about 5 minutes to baking time.)
Bake in preheated 375° oven until brown for about 45 minutes.

title: curried chicken salad with grapes
directions: Cut cooked chicken into bite size pieces.
In separate bowl, gently mix butter into mayonnaise; add garlic, parsley, curry, marjoram and pepper.
(Do not use salt; mixture is already salty.)

title: taco supper salad
directions: Into medium sized glass bowl, crumble ground beef.
Add onions to beef, mixing to blend.
Microwave on High 4 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes, or until meat loses pink color, stirring to break up meat after half the cooking time.
Drain.
Stir beans, water and taco seasoning into meat mixture.
Microwave, uncovered, at Medium 10 to 13 minutes or until thick and bubbly, stirring once. Meanwhile, tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Slice tomatoes. Chop green pepper.
In large salad bowl, toss vegetables.
Spoon meat mixture over lettuce.
Top with cheeses, then corn chips. Serve immediately with taco sauce.

title: rhubarb cherry crunch
directions: Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, salt, flour and butter.
Reserve some for topping; pat rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cut rhubarb over crust.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Place shortening in mixing bowl and beat until creamy.
Gradually add sugar to shortening, beating until light and fluffy after each addition. Add eggs and beat until thick and pale lemon in color.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately, blending thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Roll in a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans. Chill for 4 to 24 hours.

title: magic crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk and pour over butter.
Do not stir butter in.
Top with fruit and sprinkle with 1 cup sugar (use less sugar if canned fruit is used).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
To jello, add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill.
Save pineapple juice.
Heat juice and add sugar, flour and egg to it.
Cook over low heat until thickened. Cool.
Fold this mixture into small container of Cool Whip.
Pour on top of thickened jello.
Shred cheese on top of finished product.
Is very pretty and delicious.

title: hot herb bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Blend butter, parsley, oregano, garlic, dill weed and some cheese.
Spread bread slices with mixture.
Put back together and wrap in foil, leaving opening at top. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in a frying pan.
Add tomatoes, tomatoes with peppers and black-eyed peas.
Bring the mix to a boil.
Put in a casserole dish.
Prepare corn bread mix according to package directions, then pour it over casserole mix.
Bake at 375° until bread is done.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add potatoes, celery and onions.
Saute until onions are translucent.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Ladle half into blender or mash by potato masher.
(This thickens the soup). Return to heat and add milk and cheese.
Add seasonings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar substitute, baking powder, salt and spices into mixing bowl.
Combine egg, milk and shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Blend until flour is moist.
The batter should be lumpy.
Do not overmix.
Fold in minced apples.
Line, fill pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Equals 1 piece of bread.

title: cookies made from cake mix
directions: Mix all of the above.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You can roll in powdered sugar before baking.

title: blueberry pie
directions: *Can substitute fresh or frozen berries.
Use approximately 2 cups berries, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with sugar; stir gently.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours.
Just before serving, beat cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Gradually stir in liqueur.
Fold in strawberries.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup of milk and butter.
Add nuts and press half in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of milk.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on baked crust, pour on caramel and press remaining dough on top. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Make patties out of hamburger.
Place a large piece of aluminum foil in a shallow baking pan.
Place meat patties on the foil.
Slice onion, potatoes and carrots on top of meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place 3 or 4 large pats of butter on top.
Place foil over top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with A.1. steak sauce.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken in small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip cookie bar
directions: Cream butter, oil, egg, vanilla and sugars together.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; mix well. Fold in chocolate chips. Spray a 9 x 13 baking pan with nonstick spray.

title: golden goddess punch
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Yield: 75 servings.

title: chicken szechwan
directions: Remove bones from chicken breasts and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix egg white, cornstarch, salt, ginger root, soy sauce and pepper in glass bowl; stir in chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil until hot. Add chicken; stir-fry until chicken turns white, about 3 minutes. Remove chicken.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil until hot.
Add green onions, mushrooms, hoisin sauce and cayenne pepper; stir-fry about 1 minute.
Add chicken and chicken broth; heat to boiling.

title: party chicken and shrimp(yields 6 servings)
directions: In skillet, cook onion in butter until tender.
With slotted spoon, remove onion and set aside for later.
In drippings over medium heat, cook chicken until browned.
Into skillet, measure 3 tablespoons of minced parsley.
Stir in onion, tomato sauce, wine, water, salt, basil and pepper.
Over high heat, heat to boiling, then reduce to low.
Add shrimp; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until both are tender.
Skim off fat.
Spoon mixture onto warm platter.
Sprinkle with parsley.
A simple but elegant entree!!

title: supreme cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and lemon juice; set in refrigerator to thicken.
Mix cheese and vanilla and sugar.
Add to lemon mixture.
Whip Milnot to firm peaks and fold into lemon and cheese mixture.

title: 6 minute carrots
directions: Slice carrots at an angle, very thin, enough to measure 1 cup. Heat oil in skillet.
Add carrots and other ingredients; cover and lightly steam for 6 minutes, or until tender, stirring once or twice.
Makes 2 servings.
May have to add more water.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomato.
Add tomato after mixture has set overnight.

title: mother's fruit custard pie
directions: Cook evaporated peaches until tender; drain and sweeten.
Mash thoroughly and cool several hours.
When cold, line pie pan with pastry and spread layer of peaches over bottom very evenly.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place raw meat in roaster.
Place onion and celery on top of meat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven until beef is very tender and well done and will shred when picked apart.
Remove from roaster and shred with forks while still hot.
Return to sauce in roaster.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve in hamburger buns.
Makes 15 to 20.

title: microwave coffee cake
directions: Soften butter in microwave at 50% power.
Blend in sugar and mix until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and baking powder, blending until moistened well.
Pour into a greased glass baking dish.
Add topping.

title: chicken with swiss cheese
directions: Cook chicken breasts in microwave for 2 minutes per breast piece.
(Or simmer in water until tender.)
Skin the breasts and place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover each piece with sliced Swiss cheese.
Mix together the chicken soup and half and half. Pour this over the top.
Stir the croutons into the melted butter and put on top of chicken.
Bake at 325° for about 1/2 hour or until it bubbles.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Drain.
Pour in tuna, soup and peas.
Put in casserole dish and bake in oven until bubbly.

title: marshall field chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients and add eggs and vanilla. Mix flour and oatmeal together.
Put small amounts of oatmeal and flour in blender and blend until oatmeal is a powder.
Add salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients together. Add chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes. Do not overcook!

title: "special k" candy
directions: Heat peanut butter, sugar and Karo.
Add Special K. Place in greased cake pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits; spread on top.
Cool 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine rice, water, salt and margarine and bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Add corn and soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old-time rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and salt.
Pour into buttered 1 to 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 300°, stirring occasionally. Add lemon peel, nutmeg and raisins.
Continue baking for 1 1/2 hours.
Two thirds cup of brown sugar may be substituted for white sugar.

title: quick rolls
directions: Bake in muffin tins at 400° until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for 20 minutes.
Better if done a day ahead.

title: mayonnaise(blender)
directions: Mix all the ingredients with blender running on slow speed. Add 1 tablespoon of lemon juice and 1 cup salad oil.
Yield:
1 1/4 cups.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease casserole dish.
Break crackers up in milk to soften.
Set aside.
To crab meat, add salt, pepper and melted butter.
Mix, then add salad dressing, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, crackers and milk mixture; mix lightly. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 425° about 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: elegant english trifle
directions: Pour cold milk into mixing bowl.
Add egg custard mix and stir until dissolved.
Heat cream and 1/4 cup milk in top of double boiler.
Stir hot liquid into soaked custard mix.
Cook mixture over simmering water, stirring, until thick (15 to 20 minutes). Cool.
Add lemon juice and rind.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: In a 12x8x2 inch glass casserole dish, layer the following: bean dip, avocados mixed with lemon juice, sour cream mixed with taco seasoning, green onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with corn chips.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box; set aside.
Heat and mix the crab meat and additional shrimp.
Mix cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Add onion, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer half of the noodles and half of the cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, then shrimp mixture.
Repeat, reserving grated cheese for topping.
Top with peeled, sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with sugar.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together hash brown potatoes (that have been thawed) with all other ingredients, except for topping. Pour into greased 3 quart rectangular baking dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in grease.
Add to other ingredients in a casserole.
Cook in microwave 15 minutes on High.

title: italian green bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine with tomatoes and onion.
Mix in dressing and garlic salt.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: meatballs
directions: Roll into balls.
Place on baking pan and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ocean spray's best cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add cranberry sauce.
Chill until partly set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry roll
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, baking powder and salt.
Pour into well-greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350°.
Mix strawberries and sugar.
Spread strawberries and roll like jelly roll.
Slice and serve with juice from berries.
Can bake in square pan and cut into four pieces.
Serve topped with strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with chicken or as a sandwich spread.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and gradually add Sucanat.
Mix egg with lemon juice and lemon and vanilla extracts, then add to creamed Sucanat and margarine.

Mix, in separate bowl, the flour, salt and cream of tartar, then add gradually to lemon margarine mixture and beat at medium speed until mixed well. Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm enough to work with.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes and cool on wire racks.
Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water.
Stir until it thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and 1/3 cup oil.
Add flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheddar broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, onion and cheese.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
In a small bowl, mix vinegar and sugar.
Mix until sugar dissolves.
Add to broccoli mixture and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Mix potatoes with 1/2 cup melted margarine, then place in dish.
In a bowl, mix onion, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on how brown you want the topping.

title: rose's white chili
directions: Combine beans, broth, water and onion in Dutch oven.
Add chicken, chiles, cumin, oregano, red pepper and cloves.
Cook 30 minutes.
Adjust seasonings.
Serve in bowls topped with cheese. Serves 4 to 6.

title: wheat bread
directions: Mix wheat flour,
salt,
yeast	and
1	cup white flour together; set
aside.
Mix	together
margarine,
water, milk, honey
and	cottage
cheese.
Heat	thoroughly.
When
all	is melted, blended
together
and
lukewarm, remove from heat and stir in the
flour	mixture.
Add just enough of the remaining white flour to
make
a firm but sticky dough.
Place on board and knead in
remaining flour.	Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Punch down. Divide into loaves
(2	regular
loaves
or
3	small loaves). Place in greased
pans.
Cover
and let
rise
again (about 1 hour).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger and tater tots
directions: Spread hamburger in bottom of an 8-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over hamburger.
Place Tater Tots close together on top of soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Hamburger may be browned and drained to reduce fat.
Double this recipe by using one can of celery soup and 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour with salt, sugar and yeast.
Let butter melt with water.
Mix with ingredients and then add 2 to 3 more cups of flour.
Knead together.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Separate dough in 2 well-greased bread pans.
Let dough rise again.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: roz's walnut bars
directions: Mix 1/2 pound butter, cornstarch, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 2 cups flour with hands; spread in the bottom of a jelly roll pan. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Make a well; add pumpkin, eggs, oil, water and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into three greased and floured 8 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: planter's punch
directions: Mix sugar and lime juice in tall glass until sugar dissolves; add rum. Mix well. Add fruit for garnish. Fill glass with finely crushed ice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, eggs, vanilla and butter well.
Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: In skillet or wok on high heat in 2 tablespoons oil, stir-fry boneless chicken cut in strips.
Remove and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to skillet.
Stir-fry 4 cups vegetables and 1 clove minced garlic until tender-crisp.
In cup, combine 1 cup chicken broth, cornstarch, ginger and soy sauce.
Add to skillet with reserved chicken.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring often. Serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Flour and grease a loaf pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour picante sauce over chicken and bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and place cheese slices over chicken and place back in oven for 10 minutes.

title: fiddle faddle
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl and set aside. Place pecans and almonds on cookie sheet.
Toast in 350° oven for 10 minutes to make crisp.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Fold in mayonnaise, soup, cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Top with additional grated cheese and finely crumbled Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: louisiana bayou barbecue shrimp
directions: Wrap gas grill grate in tin foil to prevent sauce and shrimp from falling through.
Turn on both sides to high setting.
Mix barbecue sauce and Tabasco.
Stir until fully mixed.
Add shrimp; mix so all shrimp are covered in sauce.
Pour whole contents on foil on red hot grill.
Cook until shrimp curl up tight and start to brown and dry.
Place on plate and add just a touch more sauce to moisten.
Enjoy some good Louisiana eatin as you chaw down.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all in 2-quart casserole dish.
Crush 2 cups corn flakes; put on top.
Pour melted butter over; bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lazy peach pie
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and milk. Pour in center of butter.
Pour fruit in center of mixture (do not stir).
Cook at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream (optional).

title: fowl play
directions: Saute onion in vegetable oil lightly.
Brown chicken parts in oil.
Just barely cover with water, then add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with paprika (as much as you like).
Simmer until chicken is done, then mix about 3 tablespoons flour to a cup of milk.
Add this to the chicken and simmer until it is thick.
Very good with pasta.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Boil and drain spinach. Mix all ingredients. Place in a buttered casserole dish and dot with butter and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spirit's favorite dessert
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Serve it to your dog when you and your family are having dessert.
When serving your families yogurt, make sure you don't mix the bowls up and don't give them the dog's dessert!

title: white potato cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, potatoes and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients slowly with milk.
Add flour and nuts last.
Bake in floured pan, using butter or oleo to grease pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Stir in minced onion (or sprinkle meat with onion flakes, salt and pepper).
Stir in ketchup, mustard, brown sugar and pickle juice.
Pour into crock-pot and cook on low for at least 8 hours (a must step!); stir occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Chill the dough at least 3 hours.
Roll into 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured pastry cloth.
Cut cookies with floured cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: guacamole
directions: Cream all ingredients with spoon or a potato masher.
Prepare just before serving.

title: flan(spanish custard)
directions: Dissolve 3/4 cup sugar in water in a 9-inch round (deep 3 1/2 inch) metal pan.
Bring mixture to a boil to make caramel sauce. As soon as mixture turns a caramel color, remove it from heat and rotate pan to cover all the inside of pan.
Let it stand to cool. In another pan mix egg yolks, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Strain into caramelized pan.
Place pan in a hot water pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool.
Refrigerate until the next day.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Grease sides of pan with butter.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking pan as written.
Press firmly and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand in pan until cold.

title: hugs and kisses
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown beef.
Add onion and celery to skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine meat mixture with macaroni.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Combine mushrooms and zucchini in 1-quart microwave-safe casserole. Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Combine egg, cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Spread about 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of an 8-inch square microwave-safe baking dish.
Place half the lasagna sheets on sauce.

Layer with half the vegetables and half the cottage cheese mixture. Spoon 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce over cheese mixture. Repeat layers of lasagna, vegetables, cottage cheese mixture and remaining spaghetti sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 15 to 17 minutes or until center is heated, rotating dish once.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving. Makes about 6 servings.

title: turnip greens
directions: Combine all together in 4-quart pot and cook until tender.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust. Then take pudding and milk. Beat at low speed 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Spread more Cool Whip on top with chocolate shavings.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Combine meat with onion; saute in butter until lightly browned. Add rice, salt and thyme and mix well.
Cook cabbage leaves in boiling water for 1 minute; drain and pat dry.
Spoon meat mixture on center of leaves; fold over and secure with toothpicks.
Place on greased, shallow baking dish and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: potato ore-ida
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except 1/2 stick of margarine and the Town House crackers.
Put in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and crumble the crackers and sprinkle this mixture on the top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple nut pie cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, egg, nuts, apples, vanilla and raisins. Turn into greased pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: layered salad
directions: Prepare night before.
In large bowl, preferably glass, so that layers may be seen, layer vegetables as listed.
Cover with thin
layer of mayonnaise sprinkled with sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Top
with	eggs, tomatoes, bacon bits and Cheddar cheese. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown onion in a little of the bacon drippings.
Put beans, bacon and onion in large casserole.
Add brown sugar and vinegar. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a bowl cream sugar, margarine, and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add bananas and beat so that the batter is well mixed. Add flour, baking soda, salt and nuts and mix.
Bake for 15 - 20 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.

title: apricot-pineapple torte
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Place raw hamburger in dish; cover with onions and season. Pour can of celery soup over hamburger and onion.
Place Tater Tots over soup.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: shortcakes
directions: Sift together first five ingredients; cut in margarine.
Stir in milk and eggs.
Mix to form a dough.
Knead dough lightly on a floured surface.
Shape into half inch thick square.
Cut into nine 3-inch biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 400°. Bake 15 minutes.
Split warm biscuits and top with your favorite fresh or frozen fruit.
Yields 9 servings.

title: chewy coconut bars
directions: In medium bowl, beat butter with 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in 1 cup flour until blended.
Pat mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from oven.

title: macaroni salad
directions: After cooking macaroni, rinse; add milk and toss.
Cover bowl and chill for a short while.
In separate container mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add bouillon.
Stir together and add to macaroni. Add tomatoes, bell pepper and onion.
Add dill weed and salt to taste.

title: raspberry maple dressing(for martha's vineyard salad)
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend for 45 seconds or until all ingredients are well mixed.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Store remaining dressing in the refrigerator (will keep indefinitely).
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: mayor's supper dish
directions: Saute meat, pepper and onion until brown.
Add tomatoes and corn and simmer 15 minutes.
Add chili mix, salt and sauces and mix well.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Place mixture in large casserole.
Cover with cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: light chicken n rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in an 8 x 12 inch baking dish.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven, place rice, vegetables, 1/2 can of onions around and under chicken.
Pour broth over all.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes longer. Serve.

title: no-bake p-nut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Then add powdered sugar, mixing well.
Fill each pie crust smoothing top well.
May put in freezer for an hour or so before serving.

title: date cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients and form into 3 balls.
Roll each ball lightly in parsley or finely chopped nuts.
Also may be used for sandwich spread for parties.

title: creative dough
directions: Cook all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes, stirring vigorously until mixture forms a ball. Remove dough from saucepan and let stand on counter 5 minutes. Knead dough about 30 seconds or until smooth and blended. Cool completely. Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Roll out to about 1/4 inch and use toy or small cutters. Let dry and paint features and etc.

title: lemon pies
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and lemonade; mix well. Pour mixture into pie crusts.
Chill 1 hour.

title: orange salad or dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water and let cool.
Stir in pineapple. When it starts to thicken, mix in the ice cream.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white with 1 teaspoon of water until frothy.
Add pecans; mix well.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a 15 x 11-inch pan.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Place nuts in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture and bake at 225° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Roll balls in Angel Flake coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus tips.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Spoon mushroom soup over asparagus and add boiled eggs.
Sprinkle extra cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Layer boiled, peeled and sliced sweet potatoes into baking dish; layer with sliced apples and raisins and dot with butter. Pour maple syrup over each layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, salad dressing and chili powder.
Put cheese in and mix. Bake 20 minutes and until thoroughly heated.

title: peach pie
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, pudding, margarine, egg and milk in mixer for 2 minutes.
Spread in a deep 9 or 10-inch pie plate; push up side.
Drain peaches (save juice).
Place peaches over crust.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add yeast to creamed mixture.
Add 2 cups warm water to mixture.
Sift enough self-rising flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out on floured board; cut out and place on floured cookie sheets.
Let rise 30 minutes. Fry in deep fat and drain on paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar while hot or glaze with a thin paste of powdered sugar, hot water and vanilla.

title: apple nut bar
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Add oil gradually until thoroughly blended.
Add baking soda, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well. Add flour and mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great served warm!

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Line small loaf pans with waxed paper and pack mixture firmly into pans.
Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate.
Let set for couple of days before cutting.

title: rainbow meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 1 large or two small loaves.
Put 1/2 cup catsup on top before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
New twist of an old favorite.

title: bean sprout salad
directions: In a 5-quart pan, bring water to a boil. Cook bean sprouts in the water until just wilted (about 30 seconds).
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In a large bowl, mix vinegar, sugar, sesame oil and salt.
Add bean sprouts, pepper, ham, egg shreds and more salt to taste.
Mix and serve.

title: mother's caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks to liquid mixture gradually, then add the butter.
Let this thicken and pour in a prebaked crust, then add meringue.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until frothy, then gradually beat in sugar, a little at a time.
Next, continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Pile meringue onto pie filling, being careful to seal meringue onto edge of crust to prevent shrinking (if filling is exposed to the heat, not entirely covered, it may "weep").
Swirl or pull up points for a decorative top.
Bake on 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool gradually away from drafts to keep from falling.
